title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Boil potatoes 5 minutes until almost done.
Drain potatoes and mix in butter, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream and green onions, mixing well.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add chunky peanut butter.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix with other ingredients. Add vanilla and mix.
Add chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: slow cooker mashed potatoes(serves 6)
directions: Combine in a bowl the cream cheese, sour cream, butter, salad dressing mix and parsley; stir in potatoes. Transfer to a slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 2 to 4 hours.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Melt the oleo and marshmallows.
Pour over mixture and pack in pan.

title: chocolate pecan sheet cake
directions: Place margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour into bowl with flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost while hot with Icing for Sheet Cake.

title: green beans
directions: Cook them in a pan and eat them.

title: diana's corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs with milk; add 1 tablespoon of melted Crisco and the corn.
Combine the two mixtures lightly.
Drop from a teaspoon into deep Crisco heated to 365°.
Fry until brown and cooked in center (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Drain.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and spices.
Add pumpkin, milk and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 425° for about 1 hour or until silver knife inserted in the filling comes out clean.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, graham crumbs mixed with melted butter; press into pan.

title: some more
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
When almost done, add rice. Boil celery and water for 5 minutes.
Combine with beef mixture in a bowl.
Add soy sauce and soups.
Place in casserole.
Top with Chinese noodles.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Can be made day before; don't add noodles until ready to bake.

title: "enchilada" casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients (and optional peppers) in large pan over low heat.
Crush (in the bag) the tortilla chips and in large casserole dish alternately layer chips, chicken mixture and cheese to the top.
Garnish with cheese, crushed chips and sliced peppers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all but the last three ingredients and let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Put on the last 3 ingredients before baking.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: white creamy icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick paste, about 5 minutes.
Cook to lukewarm.
Meanwhile cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add to the paste.
Blend in the vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Add nuts.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, pumpkin pie spice and pecans; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugars until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients; mix just until moistened.
Turn into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool on wire racks.

title: gulyas soup with meat balls
directions: Mince the meat and in the heated fat, brown the chopped onion. Add the paprika pepper and the caraway seed to the browned onion. Stir and pour in one and a half pints to cold water.
Now mix the minced meat with moist bread crumbs and the egg.
Season well with salt and pepper and shape into small balls.

title: 7 layer spinach salad
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with 2 teaspoons sugar, pinch of salt and pinch of pepper.
Layer 1/2 of salad ingredients in order given, then cover with 1/2 of dressing mixture.
Repeat with rest of ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese manicotti(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, diced Mozzarella cheese, eggs, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and wheat germ thoroughly; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook manicotti tubes as directed on package; drain.
Fill tubes with cheese filling, using butter knife or teaspoon.
Place filled tubes in greased baking dish (11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Pour tomato sauce over tubes. Cover with aluminum foil; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove foil; sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes longer.

title: tofu spinach lasagna
directions: Cook the noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside on towel.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Squeeze the spinach as dry as possible and set aside.
Place the tofu, sugar, soy milk, garlic powder, lemon juice, basil and salt in a food processor or blender and blend until smooth.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with a thin layer of tomato sauce, then a layer of noodles (use about one-third).
Follow with a layer of half of the tofu filling and half of the spinach.
Continue in the same order, using half of the remaining tomato sauce and noodles and all of the remaining tofu filling and spinach.
End with the remaining noodles, covered by the remaining tomato sauce.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon beef steak
directions: Boil canned beef stock, uncovered, at least 10 minutes before tasting or using; set aside.
Rub meat with cut edge of garlic. Cut meat into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Melt butter; add meat and brown quickly.
Remove from heat; season meat with salt and paprika.
Arrange onion and lemon slices over meat.
Add 3/4 cup of the stock; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add tomato wedges; cover and simmer until tomatoes are hot, about 2 minutes. Remove meat and vegetables; keep warm.
Discard lemon slices.

title: french garlic chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Wash; season and flour chicken.
In a large skillet, pour 1 cup cooking oil and heat at high temperature.
Add chicken and saute until slightly light yellow in color.
Do not brown!
Chicken will still have blood showing.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: slow cooked oriental chicken
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, brown the chicken in oil on both sides.
Transfer to a slow cooker.
Combine the soy sauce, brown sugar, water, garlic, and ginger; pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to low; cook 4-5 hours longer or until the meat juices run clear.
Remove chicken to a serving platter and sprinkle with almonds.
Spoon juices over chicken and serve with hot rice if desired.
Serves 4-6.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Add cheese to sausage in skillet and melt.
Place by teaspoon on bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 20.
These are great to prepare ahead and freeze, may take a little longer to brown.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Mix beans, onion and olives.
Place 1/4 of mixture into each tortilla and roll.
Place the rolled tortilla into a casserole dish and pour over the enchilada sauce.
Top with cheese and bake at 375° until bubbly.
Serve topped with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, chopped green onions, avocado, etc.

title: stay moist banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients together with fork.
Pour into loaf pan and bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife around side of loaf and remove from pan.

title: no bake fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You will have living for Jesus an every day receipt.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heavily grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan, Bundt pan or two 9 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cream butter in a large bowl until smooth.
Add sugar gradually and beat well with a mixer.
Clean off beaters.
Next, blend in honey at low speed. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: On the day before the salad is needed, mix the broccoli, onion, Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar in a large bowl.
Allow to sit overnight in the refrigerator.
Two hours before serving, add the crumbled bacon and the shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serves 6.

title: snack-cake mix
directions: Before using, stir mix, then spoon loosely into measuring cup and level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Store in airtight container in cool, dry place.
Use within 1 month.
Makes about 13 cups of mix; 4 recipes follow to use this mix.
Bake on High in microwave oven for 5 minutes or until done.
Bake at 375° in a regular oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake as directed.
Let cool on rack.
Split each layer in half.

title: death by chocolate cookie
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Coarsely chop 8 squares (1 package of chocolate).
Set aside.
Microwave remaining squares in large bowl on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is melted and smooth. Stir in sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Stir in reserved chopped chocolate and nuts.
Drop by the spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 13 minutes.
Cool 1 minute and enjoy.

title: red bean soup
directions: You may add thyme, bay leaves and bell peppers, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed. drain, add mayonnaise, soup, grated cheese, crushed crackers and mix. Bake 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: heath bar cake(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over top of all.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, cocoa, milk and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; stir until mixed.
Add oatmeal and coconut if used and stir.
Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper and drop mixture by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Set until firm.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Pour half mixture in greased baking dish; cover with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Pour remaining mixture.
Top with the other 1/2 cup of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the best carrot cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; beat and add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients; add to mixture with carrots.
Bake at 375° in 3 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: marie's peanut candy
directions: Cook all together; stir until dissolved.
Barely cook from 1 1/2 hours to 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Beat until creamed and drop by spoon.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, instant onions, salt and oregano.
Stir in 3/4 cup tomato sauce.
Cut a piece of wax paper approximately 15-inches long.
Press meat mixture into 13 x 9-inch rectangle on wax paper.
Sprinkle with cheese and mushrooms. Start with narrow end of meat and roll up meat jelly roll fashion. Press seam down in greased 12
x8 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove excess drippings from dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over meat loaf and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: extra easy lasagna
directions: Partially cook lasagna noodles until nearly done in boiling salted water.
Drain.
Melt margarine and add flour to pan.
Cook 2 minutes and add the milk.
Stir until smooth.
Shred cheese and add to white sauce.
Stir until melted.
Layer 1/2 of cheese, 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 spaghetti sauce and repeat.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and oleo over low heat (slowly and stirring constantly to keep from sticking).
When melted, pour over cereal you have placed in a large bowl.
Gently stir to mix. Put powdered sugar in a large paper bag.
Place coated cereal in the sack; cover and shake until all powdered sugar is gone.
Store in freezer to keep crisp.
Makes 1 gallon ice cream bucket full.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots; mix all ingredients and mix well.

title: herb and garlic tenderloin
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine seasoning ingredients; press onto roast.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Roast approximately 50 to 60 minutes for medium rare to medium.
Remove roast when meat thermometer registers 140° for medium rare.
Let stand 15 minutes. Carve roast into slices.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: diabetic apple cake with topping(serves 8)
directions: Cream shortening and eggs. Beat in sifted flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir in water and apple juice.
Fold in apples, grape-nuts and raisins. Pour in 8-inch square pan, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until onions are clear. Add seasonings and crawfish tails. Heat through. Add flour, stirring constantly. Add chicken broth and mix well. Simmer for 15 minutes on medium-low heat. Serve over rice.

title: parmesan bundt bread
directions: Defrost 2 loaves frozen bread in wrapper.
Cut each loaf into 8 pieces.
Grease Bundt pan well.
Dip each bread piece into melted butter, then into Parmesan cheese, mixed with 1 package of onion soup mix.
Layer first 8 pieces on bottom layer and second 8 pieces on top layer of same Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Combine juices and water and bring to boil.
Add Jell-O and stir to dissolve.
Add cream cheese.
Mix well and add Coke.
Stir in cherries and pineapple and chill until firm.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine crackers, milk, eggs, salt, pepper, onion and bell pepper.
Mix well; add ground beef.
Form into balls; brown in skillet and add tomato soup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: frozen punch slush
directions: Mix and
freeze
items.
Add ginger ale, Sprite or 7-Up to partially thawed mixture when ready to serve.

title: taco chicken
directions: Mix ingredients in plastic bag; add chicken and shake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, beat egg. Add bananas, milk and oil.
Add the liquid to dry ingredients. Stir until moist.
Spoon into greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients together in a plastic bowl with cover.
Let stand for at least 10 to 15 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes on a cookie sheet.

title: sandy's chocolate mousse
directions: Combine
water
and
instant coffee granules.
Bring to boil. Add marshmallows, chocolate chips and almond flavoring. Mix well. Let set for 1/2 hour to cool.
Whip cream to peaks. Fold chocolate
mixture into whipped cream.
Line spring-form pan bottom
and
sides
with
split ladyfingers.
Spread with jelly. Pour
mousse
in.
Chill
overnight.
Remove from pan. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: tuna-stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to the directions on the package.
Drain and set aside.
Mix soup, tuna and cheese together in medium-sized bowl.
Stuff each shell with about 1 tablespoon of the mixture. Place shells side by side in a greased casserole dish.
Pour milk over shells and cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean chowder
directions: Heat oil in large pan.
Add ground beef.
Brown on medium heat, add onion and cook until onion is clear.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil on medium heat, turn to simmer and cook for 30 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: wagon wheel pie
directions: Combine flour and salt. Cut in shortening. Sprinkle water over mixture; toss with fork until dough holds together.
Roll out to a circle 1 1/2-inches larger than 9-inch pie pan.
Fit in pan and flute edges.

title: cream puff shells(pate a choux or pouf paste)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Have eggs at room temperature. High gluten bread flour is recommended also to be at room temperature. Stir flour before measuring. Combine flour and salt together. (Use sugar only if puffs are to be used with sweet filling.) In heavy saucepan, put water (or milk) and butter. Bring to rolling boil. Add flour mixture to saucepan all at once. Beat vigorously until mixture resembles mashed potatoes. Do not overbeat. Let stand 2 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating hard after each addition. Use 4 to 5 eggs. Beat until slippery look is gone. Batter must hold shape. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn oven to 350°. Bake 25 more minutes. Stuff with filling. Filling may be pudding, ice cream, chicken salad, ham salad, cheese salad.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey meatballs with chili sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients, except chili sauce, until well mixed.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes; drain on paper towels.
Heat chili sauce until hot.
Serve with meatballs.

title: cranberry cherry pie
directions: Prepare pie crusts.
Combine cranberries, sugar, cornstarch and pie filling.
Mix well.
Spoon into pie crust-lined pan.
Adjust top crust.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar on top crust before baking.

title: favorite fruit punch
directions: In a large bowl mix all together.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Heat sugar and white syrup and let come to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Krispies and pecan pieces.
Mix well and pour into a greased pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 of each:
torn tortillas, chicken, cheese and soup mixture (then second layer).
Top with cheese.
Pour chicken broth over top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly. Add 1/2 cup of hot salsa for extra spicy.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs with oil.
Add sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift soda, flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes to 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: winter cabbage salad
directions: In pan, bring first 6 ingredients to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool.
In large bowl toss cabbage, onions and peppers.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: apple turnovers
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and salt. Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle with water. Mix well. Shape dough into ball; with floured rolling pin, roll into 8 x 18-inch rectangle. Cut 1/4 cup margarine into thin slices. Starting at 8-inch side, place margarine over 2/3 of rectangle. Fold unbuttered 1/3 over middle 1/3; fold opposite end over to make 8 x 6-inch rectangle. Roll into 8 x 18-inch rectangle again. Slice 1/4 cup margarine and place on dough as previously done, repeating the process. Wrap in plastic and chill 15 minutes. Roll refrigerated dough into 18 x 8-inch rectangle. Fold lengthwise, then crosswise; wrap and chill 1 hour.

title: cheese filled meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, 1 can tomato sauce, egg, bread crumbs, onion and seasoning; mix well.
Divide mixture in half; lightly
pack 1 portion in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.

title: konbu maki with pork
directions: Rinse konbo and cut into 5 to 6 inch lengths.
Cut pork into 1/2 inch x 1/2
inch
x 2 1/2 inch strips.	Place a piece of pork and gobo on
end
of
konbu,
roll	it up and tie with kanpyo. Put konbu maki in saucepan, add enough water to fully cover and cook
on
medium-low
heat	until
tender
(about
3 hours). Drain out
water.
Add
shoyu, salt, sugar, Mirin and m.s.g. and cook additional 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream eggs (beat) and sugar.
Add flour and buttermilk.
Add other ingredients and mix well with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a greased and floured pan, 13 x 9-inch long, or Bundt pan.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Put apples and cranberries into 9-inch square Pyrex dish. Sprinkle with sugar; pour water on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix beef, bread crumbs, onions, salt, pepper and evaporated milk together lightly but thoroughly.
Put in loaf dish or pan.
Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: one cup cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a large baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk until smooth.
Pour mixture into butter pan.
Pour fruit and juice.
Spread all over. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
In saucepan bring to a boil shortening, butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar while hot.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and cinnamon. Bake in cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple buttermilk sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.
For smaller freezer, cut down on pineapple, sugar and buttermilk.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and cola.
Bake in tube pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cook oleo, yolks, sugar and milk until thick.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Frost cake.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat with mixer until blended well. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal yeast bread for bread maker
directions: Add bread flour to yeast and follow with remaining ingredients.
Bake according to bread maker's instructions.

title: audrey's congealed salad
directions: Combine and make jellos in a large bowl. Let cool but not congealed.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese, milk sugar, Miracle Whip and pecans.
Refrigerate until congealed. Serve on lettuce leaf. Enjoy!

title: spinach salad
directions: Shred spinach into bowl.
Peel and section oranges; add to spinach.
Peel and chop avocado, adding it to the salad.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla. In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients. Add to batter. Mix well. Add zucchini. Mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Makes 2 greased loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan. Cool 15 minutes on rack. Remove from pan and cover tightly for moist bread.

title: chocolate nut wafers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in chocolate.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls of dough, 2-inches apart, on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of greased glass dipped in sugar. Bake 8 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Add sour cream to cream cheese and mix until smooth.
Add the salad mix.
Stir in lemon juice and shrimp.
Cool.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all together and put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: new orleans shrimp salad
directions: Cook rice in boiling water until tender.
Drain and cool. Drain and cut shrimp in half.
Mix shrimp, rice, vegetables and lemon juice.
Add remaining seasonings and mayonnaise; stir carefully.
Serve with crisp greens, garnishing with cucumber slices and tomato slices.
Serves 4.

title: healthy bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together; pour in loaf pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple crisp
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Use Cool Whip on top when serving.

title: e z tuna noodle casserole(microwave)
directions: Open soups and place in microwave dish.
Measure 1 soup can of milk and microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir and microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir and microwave 2 minutes more.
When smooth and hot, add mushrooms, tuna, English peas and 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Microwave until hot.
Add cooked noodles and top with 1/4 cup of shredded cheese.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Using a serrated knife, slice rolls horizontally.
Try to keep rolls from breaking apart.
Place bottom half of rolls on cookie sheet.
Layer ham and cheese on rolls.
Place top half of rolls over ham and cheese. Mix margarine, garlic powder and dry mustard and pour over top of rolls.
Sprinkle tops generously with poppy seed.
Bake in 350° oven just until cheese melts.
Cut into individual servings and serve while warm.

title: frank's country creamed chicken and noodles(with mushrooms and peas)
directions: First, leave the chickens whole, but wash them thoroughly under cold running water, taking care to remove all the debris from the inside cavity.
Then liberally sprinkle them both, inside and out, with the salt, black pepper and poultry seasoning and place them side by side in a heavy 5-quart Dutch oven.
At this point, go ahead and preheat your oven to 350°.

title: crunchy bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add corn flakes and stir.
Spoon onto waxed paper and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Cut into squares.

title: oven baked pea and lentil soup
directions: Place all ingredients in an ovenproof Dutch oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered, until peas and lentils are tender.
Mix and serve.
Top each bowl with shredded Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.

title: frozen raspberry dessert
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, walnuts and butter in bowl; mix well.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crumbly, stirring every 5 minutes. Cool and crumble.
Sprinkle half the crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat egg whites in bowl.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly until stiff peaks form.
Stir in raspberries and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread in prepared pan.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Freeze until serving time. Yield:
16 servings.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients for sauce.
Add chicken wings and pineapple. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Turn a couple of times while cooking.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Cook turnips in salt water and drain.
Cook onion in oleo until tender.
Add soup and turnips.
Stir just until mixed.
Pour into casserole dish and slice cheese.
Place on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: glazed chicken in crock-pot
directions: Combine thawed orange juice concentrate in bowl along with the marjoram, garlic powder and nutmeg.
Split the chicken breasts to make 6 serving sizes.
Dip each piece into the orange juice to coat completely.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour the remaining orange juice mixture over the chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours. When done remove ingredients and thicken with cornstarch of flour mixture.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 13 g, protein 15 g, fat 7 g, calories 173.

title: no-peek skillet chicken
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, heat oil and brown chicken over medium-high heat; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms and garlic, combined with onion recipe soup mix.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 45 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Serve with not noodles; garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: butternut squash and garlic
directions: Peel and chop butternut squash into medium-size pieces. Add canola oil to the bottom of a skillet or wok. When hot, add squash. Place a cover on the pan for a few minutes. Remove cover and continue sauteing until squash is fork-tender. Add minced garlic and saute until garlic changes color. Remove from the heat and smash the squash mixture lightly.

title: diet pretzel salad
directions: Add water and strawberries together.
Bring to a boil.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Put in refrigerator.
Mix together the crushed pretzels, margarine and 1 package Sweet 'N Low.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix together the remaining ingredients with mixer.
Put over pretzels, then pour cooled jello over cream cheese mixture.
Let gel.
Put in fridge for 30 minutes.
Add Cool Whip over jello.
Enjoy.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots in 1/2 inch slices (bias sliced).
Boil 10 to 20 minutes.
In small saucepan combine brown sugar, cornstarch, ground ginger and salt.
Add orange juice.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in butter.
Pour sauce over drained carrots.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: esther's crunchy punch
directions: Let cool.
Add one bottle Realemon and two cans pieapple juice.
Mix well.
Freeze in plastic buckets or milk cartons.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Add each ingredient one by one, mixing as you go.

title: crescent beef bake
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and onion

over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheeses. Unroll crescent rolls and separate into triangles. Spread with sour cream. Roll into crescents. Place in 2 rows over cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 8 servings.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Cook 1 cup regular rice and drain.
Cook 1 package chopped broccoli and drain.
Put in bowl with rice; add 2 tablespoons finely chopped onions, 1 can mushroom soup (undiluted) and jar of Cheez Whiz (8 ounces).
Add 2 cups of cooked ham or chicken.
Mix together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 can French fried onions.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, covered with foil, then 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in meat drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Place meat in mixing bowl.
Chop onion fine.
Crush crackers fine.
Beat egg.
Add all together; mix well.
Shape into loaf. Coat top with ketchup.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar, salt, and butter. Add eggs and nutmeg, then milk. Add soda, baking powder and flour. Roll out; cut with doughnut cutter and fry in hot oil.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin, cream cheese and marshmallows in boiling water.
Add pineapple, nuts, milk and mayonnaise.
Stir to distribute evenly.
Pour in mold and refrigerate.

title: no peek beef(from ethel williams)
directions: Use no other seasonings.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 3 hours.
No peeking.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: lasagna
directions: Prepare first six ingredients (saving one garlic clove). Simmer for 2 hours.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Run in cold water. Place in large bowl strained beef, Ricotta cheese, cream cheese, crumbled Ritz crackers, 2 eggs and garlic.
Mix together.
Layer in an oblong dish: sauce, noodles, meat, Provolone cheese, and Mozzarella cheese.
Make several layers.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken like "the kernel's"
directions: Make a paste of above ingredients; spread evenly over chicken. Stack in bowl; cover and refrigerate overnight.
One hour before serving, heat oil in heavy saucepan 3 inches deep.
Deep fat fryer is set at 400°.
Dip chicken in milk or club soda.
Drain off excess.
Dust lightly with pancake flour.
Dry a few minutes.
Fry few pieces at a time.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: kentucky fried rabbit
directions: Wash dressed rabbits thoroughly.
Dry; cut into pieces. Combine eggs and the milk; add 1 cup flour gradually.
Salt and pepper and beat until smooth.
Dip rabbit into batter and fry in oil until brown, about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and continue cooking until tender, 30 to 40 minutes, turning frequently. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt, stirring until thoroughly blended. Stir in coconut.
Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 36.

title: caramel squares
directions: In skillet, melt margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased 8 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° until light brown, about 25 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil for 5 minutes; let cool.
Mix everything together and freeze.
Take out of freezer about 4 hours before serving.
Mash with potato masher.
Add 2 large Canada Dry ginger ales (cold). Serves 35.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and vanilla.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating well until smooth and creamy.
If the mixture is too thick, add a little milk.

title: company's coming squash
directions: Simmer squash, carrots, onions and pimento in small amount of water.
Line casserole dish with the stuffing and margarine, mixed.
Save out enough for topping.
Mix soup into squash mixture and blend in sour cream.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Put everything together and heat.
Put mixture into hamburger buns and serve.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Mix all together in a 3-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Microwave on High for 20 minutes.
Serves 12.
Can be cut in half.

title: horseradish carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain, but reserve 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Mix liquid with horseradish, onion, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Arrange carrots in pie plate.
Pour horseradish mix over carrots.
Mix bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle over top. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk jello salad
directions: Heat juice from pineapple.
Add jello.
Cool. Then add remaining ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: super layered salad(large tupperware bowl)
directions: Top with Parmesan cheese and toss when serving.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into balls, then roll in coconut.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Makes 6 dozen balls.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Let all stand until cold.

title: walnut spice cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients, except walnuts.
Scrape bowl. Mix on high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Fill and frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: sandra's tuna roll
directions: Combine tuna, cream cheese, onion salt and nuts.
Using wax paper, roll the mixture into a log.
Sprinkle lemon pepper and paprika to taste over the log.
Cover with parsley flakes.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in hot water. Add fruit and pour into mold or casserole dish. Set in refrigerator and let congeal.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Bake in a buttered dish for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and top with dressing, mixed with 1/2 cup margarine. Bake 10 minutes more.

title: two-corn bread
directions: Stir together flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Beat eggs and cottage cheese until smooth; stir in corn.
Add to other ingredients; stir to blend.
Bake at
375° in a 9-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles until done.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine all the other ingredients except the stove top stuffing.
Add noodles, put into 9x9 in. greased baking dish.
For topping, cover with Stove Top Stuffing and a little extra cheddar cheese.	Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes until bubbly.

title: chocolate yum-yum
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler (can microwave). Mix the sugar, water and egg yolks. Add to chocolate. Cook until thick, stirring this into chocolate mixture. Add vanilla and nuts. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into mixture. Begin with vanilla wafers and alternate layers between wafer and chocolate in 8 x 11 inch dish. Refrigerate. Cut in squares and top with whipped cream.

title: pickled zucchini
directions: Wash, remove stem and blossom ends and cut squash into 1/4-inch rounds.
Peel and slice onions.
Sprinkle salt over combined zucchini and onion.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand 1 hour. Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed, turmeric and dry mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Heat to simmering 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: baked round steak
directions: Spread butter on steak.
Sprinkle mushrooms, then dry soup mix over steak.
Wrap in two thicknesses of foil and place on covered roaster with rack (a cookie sheet also works).
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Place broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon into a bowl.
Set aside and refrigerate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add eggs beaten with some of the milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add remaining milk and water; stir until well mixed.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Add butter and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Recipe easily doubles.
Real good.

title: world war i cake
directions: Boil together 5 minutes the first 7 ingredients.
After mixture begins to bubble, set aside to get cold.
Add flour and soda, dissolved in water.
Mix well.
Bake in greased tube pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue cube steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cube steaks and oil. Brown the cube steaks on each side in the oil.
Add the barbecue sauce to the steaks, both sides, and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Turn and baste 2 or 3 times during simmer.

title: easy brisket
directions: Melt butter.
Add lemon juice, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Put brisket in deep dish.
Pour sauce over brisket.
Cover with foil.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Chop corn.
Add salt, pepper, beaten egg, melted fat, milk, flour and baking powder.
Mix together lightly and drop by spoonfuls into deep fat (360° to 370°).
Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until brown.
Drain on brown paper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan, layer frozen rolls in pan.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon; pour over rolls.
Pour nuts, brown sugar and vanilla pudding over rolls.
Slice butter and dot over rolls.
Cover pan with towel, let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9-inch baking pan. Combine sugar and 1 tablespoon flour in small bowl.
Place apples in separate bowl; sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Toss lightly to mix.
Place in prepared pan.
Combine oats, remaining 3/4 cup flour, brown sugar and butter in small bowl; toss lightly to mix. Sprinkle over apples.
Press mixture lightly into apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix with fork the brown sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, butter or margarine and egg.
Pour half of mixture in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread can of cherry (or any other type you like) pie filling in pan mixture.
Sprinkle remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for about 2 minutes. This makes a large bar pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: crescendo corn bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Stir in corn meal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening; beat with rotary or electric beater until just mixed.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: relish
directions: Combine vegetables and salt; let set overnight.
Drain, but do not press down.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to vegetable mixture.
Bring to rolling boil, uncovered.
Reduce to simmer for 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal in boiling water process for 10 minutes.
Yield: 5 or 6 pints.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind all vegetables.
Put the salt over them and soak overnight.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Add to vegetables. Bring to boil.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: italian pasta bake
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Drain.
Stir in mostaccioli, spaghetti sauce and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese and remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375 for 20 minutes.

title: delicious brat casserole
directions: Saute celery until partially done.
In a well-buttered 2-quart casserole dish, place potatoes, thinly sliced.
Cut brats into 1-inch pieces.
Cook thoroughly.
Drain grease off and place on top of sliced potatoes.
Place green beans and celery over brats. Mix soup and milk.
Stir well and pour over ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can use Italian sausage.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add other ingredients, except sour cream.
Congeal half of mixture.
Add sour cream and second half of Jell-O mixture; congeal.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in a large bowl in the microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High power.
Gradually add powdered sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Pat into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and sifted flour.
Mash bananas and mix in.
Add nuts.
Mixture will be hard to stir. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: french stew
directions: In deep baking dish, layer starting with potatoes, meat and carrots.
Sprinkle onion, salt and pepper to taste.
After 2 to 3 layers, pour 1 cup of wine over entire contents.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: homemade bread
directions: Soak cake yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Mix together 1 cup of sugar, 2 Tbsp. salt and 3 1/2 cups liquid warm potato water. Add yeast mix, 1/4 cup shortening and 4 cups of flour. Mix together well. Add 7 more cups of flour, one cup at a time until dough is soft. Sometimes it doesn't take all 7 cups. Knead on floured surface. Put in greased bowl, turn, and cover; let rise until doubled.
Divide into 3 balls and place a ball of dough into each of 3 greased loaf pans. Cover and let rise again about 45 minutes. Bake 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: aunt kitty's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar.
Bring to boil; let boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pie plate, whichever one you have.
Swirl in melted chocolate.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Beat in both sugars. Stir in egg and vanilla. Add flour and baking soda.
Add peanut butter chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Press flat with fork.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Fry or microwave bacon crisp.
Brown sausage and onion.
Cube bread into large cubes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage and onion over bread.
Beat eggs and add 2 cups milk.
Beat and pour over bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Dilute soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over quiche.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt together.
Add milk.
Cool until warm.
Add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
When cool, pour into cooked, cooled pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar for each white.
Bake in hot oven until brown.
Before baking, add coconut to top of egg whites.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with tinfoil.
Place graham crackers as close as you can on cookie sheet.
Mix butter and brown sugar and cook until bubbles.
Add pecan pieces.
Pour over graham crackers. Cook in oven at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: old-fashioned blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter; add brown sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
The hand is best for this job.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Sift together soda, salt, spices and flour. Combine jam and sour milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients and jam mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.
Divide batter between two 8-inch layers.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Use caramel icing.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in hot fat. Combine other ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and mashed bananas. Sift flour and soda together.
Pour ingredients into loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick melted margarine and 1 egg (will be sticky). Spray pan (13 1/2 x 8 or 9-inch) with oil or margarine. Press mixture into pan. Pour nuts over this. Soften cream cheese and 1/2 stick margarine. Add confectioners sugar and 2 eggs. Mix and pour over nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple ice cream
directions: Place all ingredients in ice cream freezer, filling to line with carbonated orange drink.
Freeze as you would regular ice cream.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and microwave 10 to 12 minutes, rotating and stirring every 3 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips as a dip or over tortilla chips as a meal.

title: mexican salad(fills 4-quart casserole)
directions: Brown meat and add seasoning following directions on seasoning package.
Crunch up Doritos (but not too small).
Chop and mix all other ingredients (except Doritos and dressing).
Add meat to rest of salad and mix.
Add dressing and Doritos.

title: jackie's mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Mix soups and tomatoes with 1 can of chicken broth.
Put a heavy layer of chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Add a layer of chicken, then add about half of soup mixture.
Add a layer of cheese.
Continue in this manner, ending with a layer of crushed chips on top.
Put in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in cold oven.
Cook at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test with a toothpick to see if it is done.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Cream sugar and Crisco and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add flour.
Beat well.
Add pineapple and several tablespoons of juice.
Start in a cool oven.
Turn oven to 300°.
Cook approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, milk and vanilla flavoring.
Stir in coconut.
Put in pie shells.
Makes 2. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: another sugar-free idea
directions: Boil cloves in water.
Strain and use 1 cup water in making the jello (use sugar free strawberry or raspberry).
Add applesauce.

title: tropical fruit smoothie
directions: In blender combine all ingredients, except ice; blend well. Gradually add ice; blend until smooth.
Serve immediately. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press ground meat 3/4 to 1-inch deep in bottom of baking dish. Spread soup evenly over meat.
Layer Tater Tots evenly over soup. Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix ingredients together. Form into one inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased sheet until golden brown. Makes about 6 doz.
Can be frozen uncooked.

title: skip-a-step lasagna(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
In separate bowl, stir together cottage cheese, eggs, 1/3 cup Parmesan and Italian seasoning.
In 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, place 3 noodles.
Spread 1/3 of the meat/sauce mixture over noodles.
Top with 1/2 eggs, 1 cup cheese and 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella and 1/4 Swiss.
Repeat as many times as possible, ending with the meat/sauce mixture on top.
Pour boiling water around edge of lasagna.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until noodles are tender.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, butter and soda in a heavy, 3 to 4-quart saucepan and cook slowly until mixture reaches the soft ball stage, 236°.
Add vanilla, pecans and salt.
Cook 1 minute. Remove from heat and beat until mixture thickens.
Drop by tablespoons on wax paper or a buttered marble slab.
Makes 40.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, lower temperature to 350° and cook for 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruit.
Put in bowl.
Add strawberries last.
Mix pudding and juices.
Add juice to fruit.
Can also add pecans if desired.

title: hungarian crescent cookies
directions: Cream together by hand.
Roll out small portions at a time as thin as possible.
Cut into squares.
Apply filling of choice and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Brush top with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: noodle-cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Cook onion and garlic in oleo until tender, not brown.
In large bowl combine noodles, onion, garlic, cottage cheese, sour cream, 1/2 of Cheddar, steak sauce, salt, basil and dash of pepper.
Put into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine Ranch dressing mix with sour cream and mayonnaise. Pour over chopped vegetables and chill overnight.

title: crab cakes - maryland style
directions: Blend all the ingredients thoroughly.
Then make into about 3-inch cakes.
Use a wide, heavy frying pan if possible.
Lightly oil and heat to medium temperature.
Cook the cakes until brown on both sides and serve immediately while hot.
Use sauce, if desired.

title: cube steak supper
directions: Flour and brown cube steak.
Place into large casserole dish. Peel and quarter the potatoes and put over the meat.
Add the carrots.
Mix mushroom soup, milk and water; pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover.
Top with cheese; bake until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: dump cake
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour filling in pan. Sprinkle drained tidbits.
Cut in pieces on top, then cake mix dry.
Pour melted butter (oleo) over this.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Delicious served with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: baked popcorn crunch
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Mix in warm popcorn and nuts.
Spread in large pan (jelly roll or broiler pan).
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: many layers salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, tear lettuce and cover bottom of pan. Pour peas evenly over lettuce.
Spread chopped tomatoes evenly. Spread chopped water chestnuts evenly.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over vegetables.
Spread shredded Colby evenly over mayonnaise. Sprinkle bacon over Colby.
Shake a light layer of Parmesan over bacon.
Great side dish!

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples and slice thinly.
Stir together Sugar Twin, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt to blend and mix lightly with apples.

title: spanish cornbread
directions: Pour half the batter into a greased pan.
Place layer of chilies, layer of cheese and then remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: spice swirl coffee cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes until creamy.
Pour 1/3 of batter into prepared tube pan; sprinkle with 1/2 sugar mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla and fold in nuts and apples.
Grease and flour pans.
Can be baked in a bundt or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours, a 13x9x2 inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes, 3 8 inch cake pans for 35 minutes or 2 loaf pans for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate-mint fudge bars
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Cool.
Add eggs, extract and sugar.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour and salt and beat until blended.
Spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add graham cracker crumbs and press down.
Beat two sticks margarine, eggs and powdered sugar for 10 minutes. Pour over graham crackers.
Slice bananas over egg mixture.
Add drained pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: kolachky
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Add crumbled yeast.
Cut in butter.
Add the egg yolks, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and divide dough into 6 equal parts.
Dust counter with powdered sugar and roll each piece of dough in a circle and cut into 8 parts.
Place a spoonful of filling on each wedge of dough and roll toward center.
Sprinkle generously with powdered sugar before rolling dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove immediately and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 4 dozen kolachkies.

title: italian beans parmesan
directions: In skillet, saute onion and pepper in butter until soft.
Add potatoes; saute 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook over high heat until slightly thickened.
Add beans; heat through.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation and cook time: 20 minutes.

title: frito bean salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and let set in refrigerator most of the day, then just before serving, add crushed Fritos.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken breasts.
Add all the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Add more seasoning and mayonnaise, if needed. Sprinkle with paprika and decorate with fresh parsley.

title: hint: for crisp curtains
directions: Dissolve Epsom salts in sink of water.
Rinse curtains in this water and let dry.

title: cheese ring
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat milk and butter to rolling boil in 2-quart saucepan.
To flour, mix nutmeg and pepper.
Combine cheeses.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in 4 eggs all at once; continue beating until smooth.
Fold in 2/3 cup of cheese.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet to form 8-inch ring.
Smooth with spatula.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until puffed and golden, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lacy peanut cookies
directions: Bring corn syrup to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Continue cooking over low heat, stirring constantly until peanut butter and butter are melted and well blended.
Remove from heat and stir in oats, brown sugar and flour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 3-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cook 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Remove and cool. Drizzle melted chocolate over cookies.

title: sugar-free banana split pie
directions: Note:
One-fourth pie equals 1 bread, 1 fruit and 1 milk. Contains 50 calories.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into shallow pan.
Layer shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, shredded cheddar cheese, chopped black olives and serve with nacho chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and make small balls.
Bake in an oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Add Cool Whip last.
Sets up fast. Good.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Pound each chicken breast until flat.
Prepare stuffing following package directions (1 cup for every 2 chicken breasts). Place a ball of stuffing in the middle of each breast.
Fold breast around stuffing and pinch together at top and sides.
Place in a buttered baking dish and brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with stuffing crumbs and pour cream over the top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi with angel hair pasta
directions: In large saucepan boil water for pasta.
In separate saucepan boil shrimp briefly until color changes and drain.
In broiling pan or shallow baking dish combine olive oil, butter, lemon juice, wine, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add shrimp and coat with mixture.
Place shrimp in single layer in broiling pan and top with bread crumbs and parsley.
Pour some of oil/butter mixture over bread crumbs to moisten.
Broil for approximately 5 minutes or until bread crumb topping browns.
Cook pasta and drain. Serve shrimp over pasta and top with grated Parmesan.
Spoon on remaining oil/butter mixture.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fill with cut up rhubarb, sugar, strawberry Jell-O and marshmallows.
Pour cake mix over ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn upside down while still warm.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Use a yellow cake mix and make by directions for cupcakes.

title: buck's tortilla soup
directions: Smoke chicken in a slow smoker with pecan or hickory wood. Brush on butter during cooking.
Debone and peel off skin.
Place in bowl to set aside.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in oil and 1 cup of water, mixing well.
Add remaining cup water, vinegar and vanilla. Pour into prepared pan; bake for 45 or 50 minutes, or until done. Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to the flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Peel and slice or use whole.
Pour vinegar and remaining ingredients over beets and bring to boil. Put in jars and seal.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Melt cheese in evaporated milk in heavy saucepan at low heat. Brown meat in a medium size skillet at medium heat.
Drain; season with salt and garlic salt.
Heat 1/2-inch shortening in a heavy skillet at medium-high heat; quickly dip each tortilla into the shortening to soften.
Drain on absorbent towels.
Layer all ingredients except cheese sauce in a greased, 2-quart casserole dish, beginning with tortillas.
Pour cheese sauce over layered ingredients and cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream puffs(yields 50 portions)
directions: Melt margarine in boiling water.
Add flour and salt, all at once, to boiling mixture.
Beat vigorously.
Remove from heat as soon as mixture leaves sides of pan.
Transfer to mixer bowl. Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating on high speed after each addition.

title: crushed banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well with mixer.
Add nuts.
Bake in 350 degree oven until done.

title: apricot applesauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine apricots and lemon slices.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer until apricots are tender.
Add more water, if necessary, to prevent sticking.
Add applesauce and blend well.
Add sugar to taste. Reheat until mixture starts to bubble.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 cups. Very good served with Country Ribs With Sauerkraut.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: company sweet potatoes
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 25 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: In pan, combine juice, onions, cinnamon and vinegar. Heat to boiling and pour over beets. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: frozen vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Drain.
Add celery and onions.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese and add vegetables.
Pour into a casserole.
Melt margarine and add to crumbled crackers. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp pie
directions: Pour over shrimp.
Serve with crackers.
This can be made a day before serving.

title: cinnamon-vanilla pull apart bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spray loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. In small bowl, combine cinnamon vanilla, spice blend and sugar; mix well. Cut each biscuit into quarters. Dip each piece into melted butter; roll in cinnamon mixture. Arrange in prepared loaf form. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool 2 minutes. Loosen edges; invert onto serving plate. Serve warm.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil and eggs; stir in nuts and strawberries.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check after 1 hour.

title: grandma rosie's musical butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add slightly beaten egg.
Gradually blend in flour.
Put in cookie press.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased preheated 400° oven.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook until thick.
Add mayonnaise as desired.

title: unusual tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place onions, then roast in crock-pot.
Add potatoes and carrots on top of roast.
Combine the soup with small amount of water; pour over roast.
Cover and cook on high for around 8 hours or low for about 12 hours.

title: chicken and asparagus
directions: Brown chicken breasts.
Season with salt and pepper in oil. Cook asparagus.
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Place chicken soup mix and asparagus in layers. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Place in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces.
Place sugars and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Add biscuit pieces, a few at a time, and shake. Place pieces in greased tube pan.
Layer with pecans, raisins or coconut, if desired.
Repeat layers of biscuit pieces until all are used.

title: no-knead golden loaves
directions: Combine water, yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes; mix well.
Gradually add flour to form stiff dough. Mix well until blended, about 2 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise in warm place (85° to 90°) until doubled in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Toss lightly on well-floured board to coat dough with flour.
Divide in half; shape into 2 round loaves. Place in two 6-inch casserole dishes which have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover; let rise until doubled (30 to 60 minutes).
Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: fish fillets in garlic butter
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute garlic 1 minute.
Place fish over garlic; cover and cook over low heat 3 minutes.
Carefully turn fish; sprinkle with onions.
Cover and continue to cook until fish flakes easily with a fork, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Squeeze lemon over fish.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: gazpacho chicken salad
directions: Chop and mix the peppers and onion. Whisk together olive oil, vinegar, garlic, salt, cumin and pepper. Add peppers and onion mixture to this and chill for 1 hour. Layer in a glass casserole: the lettuce, bell pepper mixture and chicken. Serve cold.

title: hamburger and cabbage dish
directions: Brown hamburger in saucepan; drain.
Add all other ingredients at once and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
(V-8 juice can be used in place of tomato juice.)
Serve with potatoes or rice.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Rinse chicken, then pat dry.
Place chicken in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt butter in saucepan, stir in all remaining ingredients (except rice) and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve chicken and gravy over cooked rice.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Wash eggplant and slice 3/4 inch thick.
Dip slices in flour, then egg, then bread crumbs.
Should be well coated.
Saute in olive oil a few at a time until browned.
Tend carefully, add oil if needed.
When crisp and brown, place in shallow baking dish. Put cheese slice on each slice.
Dilute tomato paste with wine, mix in oregano, salt, pepper and crushed garlic clove.
Spread over eggplant.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Mix Jell-O as usual.
Add berries, bananas and pineapple together.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a bowl.
Let set.
Spoon sour cream over Jell-O.
Pour remaining Jell-O over sour cream.
Let set.
Enjoy.

title: banana split pie
directions: The first 2 ingredients are for pie crust; mix as for pie crust and put into cake pan.

title: pita bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, corn syrup, soda and margarine in saucepan.
Cook to 234° to 240° on candy thermometer (soft ball stage).
Add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: special kielbasa
directions: Cook kielbasa in water and set aside.
Chop cabbage and onion and fry with margarine/oil in frypan until limp and browned.
Cut up cooked kielbasa in slices and add to cabbage along with crushed tomatoes and juice.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Carrots can be added for color.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6-inch), melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle in crumbs; stir well.
Press on bottom of dish.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Good with Ritz crackers or chips.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into small balls or drop from spoon.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not grease cookie sheet.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and slice vegetables.
Put all ingredients, except milk and chives, in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).
Stir in milk during last hour.
Serve topped with chives.

title: fusilli with onion and bacon
directions: Place porcini in bowl with lukewarm water to cover and soak, until softened, about 30 minutes.
Drain.
In large frying pan, heat 4 tablespoon of oil, add onions and saute, stir until golden brown.
Add wine and porcini season with salt and pepper.
Heat remaining olive oil, add bacon and saute.
In large pot, boil salted water; add fusilli and cook.
Add the contents of the bacon pan and cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.

title: red snapper with tomato sauce
directions: On sheet of wax paper or a paper plate, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge fish in flour mixture, coating both sides.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.

In saucepan, add butter, oil, cocoa, Coca-Cola and marshmallows. Bring to a boil and cool. Add to flour and sugar, then add soda, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: red, green and white salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water and cool.
Add pineapple when it begins to set.
Pour into a mold and chill until set.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water and cool.
Add whipping cream to cottage cheese and beat.
Add lemon jello when it begins to set.
Pour over congealed lime mixture and chill until firm.
Dissolve red jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Cool and pour over salad.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Put in refrigerator to chill about 1 hour, then form cheese ball into whatever shape you want, round, egg-shaped, etc.
Serve cold for best results with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine with all other ingredients in a Dutch oven, casserole dish or crock-pot.
You may need to add some chicken broth to make it creamy.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk together until thickened.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Make layers of graham crackers and pudding.

title: treva's peanut butter roast
directions: Combine in blender.
Pour into wax paper-lined bread pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookie mix
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and both sugars in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mix is crumbly.
Stir in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator or freezer for up to 6 months.

title: baked-filled zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp.
Salt and pepper.
Melt butter. Saute onion, celery and ground beef.
Add bread crumbs and the scooped out pulp with tomato sauce.
Stir together.
Stuff zucchini.
Place in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grandma armstrong's loaf bread
directions: Combine warm water, yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let set until foamy and bubbly; set aside.
Scald milk and Crisco.
Dissolve 1/4 cup sugar and salt in this.
Let cool.
When this is just warm, add 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir in enough flour until thick like pancake batter.
Add yeast mixture to this.
Keep adding flour until the dough is not sticky.
Knead.
Let dough rise 2 times, kneading each time. Place dough in 2 greased pans and let dough rise again.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 2 loaves.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce up; put first layer lettuce, then layer English peas, lettuce, onion, lettuce, pepper, lettuce, bacon bits and eggs.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Spread cheese over the top.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix the egg white and water. Add pecans.
Leave in mixture until well moistened.
Mix the sugar, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg. Mix with the nuts.
Place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Store in airtight container.

title: green beans and pearl onions
directions: In saucepan of boiling water, cook onion for 3 minutes. Remove to bowl.
Cook beans 6 minutes in same water.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Peel onions.
In large skillet, melt butter in oil over medium heat.
Add onions and stir occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes, until browned.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, until hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburg and onions.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.

title: scampi
directions: Place olive oil in a heavy skillet and add salt, pepper and garlic.
Heat until garlic is golden.
Add shrimp, wine and lemon juice.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Shake the pan from time to time and spoon some of the liquid over the shrimp.
Place the shrimp in soup bowls and pour the savory liquid over.
Sprinkle generously with parsley.
Serve with rice.
Serves 2.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan (or similar). Drop cream cheese chunks on top of beans.
Brown and drain beef.
Mix in seasoning. Spread meat over beans and cream cheese.
Pour salsa over the top evenly.
Cover with shredded cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 40 minutes.
Let stand at least 15 minutes to set.
Eat with the chips.

title: garden row salad
directions: Put carrots in blender container; cover with cold water. Cover with lid and blend until coarsely chopped.
Drain and set aside.
Repeat process with cucumber, then celery.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium saucepot.
Heat on medium for 9 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally, until Cheddar cheese melts and mixture is warm.
Serve in a hollowed out round loaf of rye, sourdough or pumpernickel bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in casserole, 9 x 13-inch.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.

title: old-fashion chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, eggs, buttermilk, salt, soda and vanilla.
Add hot water and mix.
Add flour and cocoa; mix thoroughly.
Bake 30 minutes.
DON'T overbake.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first four ingredients to a boil for 1 minute.
Mix last four ingredients and then add to boiled mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Drain orange slices.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into graham cracker crust and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all except peaches and toss with peaches.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Top with pastry or crumb topping. Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: nana's lemon pudding
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Stir
in
3	egg
yolks,
beaten.
Mix with milk. Fold in 3 stiffly beaten egg whites.	Pour in custard cups and bake 45 minutes at 375° (over water).

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Beat sugar into egg whites.
Fold in Ritz crackers.
Fold in 3/4 cup pecans; reserve 1/4 cup for top. Bake in ungreased pie pan, pushing up the edge of the pie pan. Bake at 350° until done.
Cool.

title: cornbread dumplings
directions: Boil ham bone in large pot with salt and pepper and crushed red pepper to your taste.
Take about 1 cup broth.
Cool.
Mix with meal, flour and eggs.
Add only enough broth to make a stiff batter.
Wet hands and make small cakes from batter.
Drop into boiling broth.
Cook 10 minutes uncovered and cover on low heat for 25 minutes.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in a 7 1/2 x 12-inch ovenproof dish. Combine oats, flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl; cut in butter.
Sprinkle oat mixture over apples.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Turn dish one-quarter turn; repeat cooking steps 2 more times.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all in one bowl.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Cover with cold water and ice.
Let soak 3 hours.
Combine sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed in a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Add drained cucumbers and onions. Return to a boil.
Put in hot jars. Seal jars.
Yields 6 quarts or 12 pints.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet; drain excess fat and season with salt and pepper.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook lasagne noodles.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, apricot nectar and lemon extract.
Add cake mix and jello.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Leave in pan.
Mix 4 tablespoons lemon juice and confectioners sugar.
Punch holes in cake and pour mixture over top.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Pour into crock-pot along with the rest of the ingredients and cook slow all day.
Remove bay leaf when sauce is done.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together to consistency of a sponge.
Let rise until double, knead, make into any style rolls, let rise and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet candied yams mallow(lola's recipe)
directions: Use a large casserole dish.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: pollo rosamarina(chicken rosemary)
directions: Clean and quarter chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix olive oil, chopped basil, oregano, rosemary, lemon juice, garlic and basil.
Brush on the chicken heavy.
Place on a tray.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 25 minutes on each side.
Brush on liquid to prevent dryness.
When ready, pour rest of the liquid over chicken.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Put in enough water to simmer and meat grease.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, pepper and salt.
Simmer about 30 minutes and add chili beans.
Simmer a little while longer.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and Ro-Tel.
Add chicken.
Tear corn tortillas and line bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken soup mixture and sprinkle with cheese and onions; layer, ending with cheese and onions on top.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 9-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle top with 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese and grated 1/2 pound Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, combine the flour, sugar and butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix together eggs, sugar, lemon juice, flour and baking powder.
Pour onto baked base and continue baking at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Fill jar with hot brine.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
Let cool.

title: turketti
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
About 1 hour before serving, heat oven to 350° and bake until mixture is bubbly throughout.

title: 6 biscuits
directions: Mix Crisco into flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend well.
Add milk.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut into 6 biscuits. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 450° until browned.

title: teriyaki
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar, ginger and garlic together.
Add water; mix and add meat to sauce and put in refrigerator.
Let stand overnight.
Stir next morning.
Place on baking sheet and bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until done.
Turn halfway through cooking.

title: cheesy muffins
directions: Mix everything together and beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Fill greased 12 muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hot dish
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown hamburger.
Brown celery and onion in a little butter.
Put noodles, hamburger, celery and onion along with salt and pepper in casserole.
Mix.
Combine soups and milk.
Pour over noodle mixture.
Mix.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with half the gingersnaps.
Stir together the pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices; fold into the ice cream.
Spread half over the gingersnaps.
Lay on second half of gingersnaps and spread remaining half of pumpkin mixture. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares.
