Serve with whipped cream.
Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°; butter muffin tins.
Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Break egg into a small bowl.
Add melted butter and milk; stir both into egg.
Pour over dry ingredients and beat briefly to blend.
Shake a little flour over the berries to coat them and fold gently into the batter.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 20 minutes.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Poke holes in cake while hot.
Bring the pineapple (with juice) and 1 cup sugar to a rapid boil.
Let this mixture cool awhile as you are "rocking and rollin" while cleaning your work area.
When mixture is cool, pour over cake.
Let this cool completely before icing.
Mix the confectioners sugar, butter, cream cheese, vanilla and pecans and spread on cake.

title: buried treasure dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and place half in the bottom of an 11 x 17-inch pan.
Save the rest for the top.
Use a mixer to blend whipped topping, cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.

title: fresh-pack dill pickles(unsweetened)
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly.
Scrub with a vegetable brush and drain.
Cover with brine.
Let set overnight.
Drain.
Combine vinegar, salt, water and mixed pickling spices tied in a clean, white cloth bag or spice ball.
Heat to boiling.
Pack cucumbers in hot, sterilized quart jars.
Add mustard seed, garlic and dill plant or seed to each jar.
Cover with boiling liquid to within 1/4-inch of top of jar.
Adjust seals and process in a boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer the flour tortillas, meat mixture and cheese, then repeat.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add bananas and blend in Bisquick. Pour into small muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: dried beef pinwheels
directions: Mash cheese; mix with Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Spread on beef slices; roll up and place in refrigerator until chilled. Cut into 1/2-inch lengths.
Slice carrot thin.
Place slice of carrot on toothpick, then dried beef.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown; drain. Stir in taco seasoning mix.
Spread in plate; sprinkle with chiles.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate. Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut off crust and cut each slice of white bread in 5 pieces using 10 slices of bread.
Dry for 30 to 40 minutes in 200° oven. Heat 1/2 cup oil and 10 ounce jar of peanut butter until blended. Mix 2 cups graham cracker crumbs and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Roll bread sticks in peanut butter mixture, then in sugar/cracker mixture.
Lay out on paper towel.
Let sit a few minutes, then re-roll.
(May double recipe.)

title: hasty-tasty beef stew
directions: Combine onion, celery, soups, Worcestershire sauce and meat in a large Dutch oven.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Bake an additional 30 to 45 minutes, until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Ritz crackers and 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Top with 1/2 box crumbled cheese Ritz crackers and 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly around edges.

title: coffee cake rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast.
In large bowl, combine flour, salt and vanilla; add 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in oleo.
In separate bowl, combine the eggs, milk and yeast, then add to the flour mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough, roll out; sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon.
Roll up and cut.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with hand.
Bake at 350°.
Repeat with rest of dough.

title: apple bread
directions: In bowl combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt, set aside.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt margarine and sugar and let cool;
beat in eggs and add vanilla.
Add flour and nuts and mix well.
Pour in greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When you take it out of the oven, put a wet paper towel over top of it until Chewy Cake is cool.
Cut in squares.

title: adobo chicken
directions: Peel whole garlic.
Mash.
Add all ingredients to pot and cook for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Can also be made in crock-pot.

title: breadsticks
directions: Put 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast into food processor. Add oil and hot water and process 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup more flour and process again.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a board and cut into 20 or 16 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into a rope 16 to 20 inches long. Put on a cookie sheet that is well-oiled, rolling to grease all sides of the dough.
Leave about 1-inch between each.
Now freeze or bake.
If you freeze, thaw and let rise 15 minutes.
Paint with egg wash and sprinkle with seeds.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: a cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dice bananas and measure.
Add to dry ingredients along with oil, vanilla, eggs, pineapple and juice and nuts.
(Stir, do not beat.)

title: instant egg nog
directions: Mix pudding mix and sugar in large bowl.
Beat egg yolks and strain into milk.
Add mixture, beating at lowest speed on mixer. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Chill; shake or stir before serving.
Very good.

title: jezebel spread
directions: In a medium bowl, mix cereal, peanuts, jelly beans and dates or raisins or both with a wooden spoon.
Store in a jar or a plastic container with a tight lid.

title: middle eastern turkey saute(yields 4 to 6 servings)
directions: In a medium bowl, stir coriander, turmeric and garlic powder into yogurt.
Set aside.

title: snack crackers
directions: Put crackers in a large bowl. Sprinkle on top the package of powdered dressing. Add seasonings and oil.
Mix well.
Allow oil to dry into crackers before pudding in an airtight container.

title: watergate cake
directions: Cream all together.
Pour into a greased (9 x 13-inch) pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lady meat balls
directions: Combine rice, meat, onion, parsley, cheese, 2 tablespoons of the olive oil, egg whites, dill and pepper in a bowl.
Knead well and form into twenty egg shaped ovals.
Roll ovals in flour.
Heat remaining oil over medium heat in a large frying pan.
Saute ovals for about 5 minutes, until brown on one side.
Turn carefully and saute other side for 3 minutes or until brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Keep in a covered casserole in a warm oven until ready to serve.
If refrigerating to serve later, reheat in a covered casserole at 325° for 20 minutes, until warm.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix beef with
water and rest of ingredients.
Place in crock-pot on high
for
12 hours.
Stir occasionally to shred. Serve on buns.

title: whipping boy potato chips
directions: Wash and slice potatoes (slice paper thin).
Drop into hot oil in a large frying pan. Fry until crisp and golden brown.
Remove from oil and drain well on paper towels.
Sprinkle with cheese and salt. Serve right away!

title: apple cake
directions: You need 3 bowls.
For bowl #1, combine the sugar with apples and set aside.
For bowl #2, sift together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
For bowl #3, beat eggs and add oil and vanilla.
Alternately add the ingredients from bowl #1 and 2. Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° (325° if glass dish) for 45 to 60 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar or use your favorite frosting.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with half of the whole crackers. Combine in saucepan the beaten eggs, sugar, margarine and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove and add coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread over crackers, then cover mixture with whole graham crackers.
Put frosting over graham crackers. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Cut in bars.
Makes 70 party size bars.

title: sweet and spicy chicken wings
directions: Take package of dressing mix, honey and orange juice; mix together (set aside 1/4 cup for dipping).
Marinate chicken wings at least 1 hour, then broil 5 minutes on each side until chicken is cooked and glazed.
Serve with sauce.
Very tasty and easy.

title: lemon lush
directions: Cream together; spread over the first layer.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Boil and simmer water and raisins about 20 minutes (cover with lid).
Beat eggs with wire whip in bowl.
Mix sugar and cornstarch; mix in with eggs; add milk.
Add to cooked raisins and cook to boil.
Remove from stove; add vanilla and butter.
Cool and refrigerate.
May top with Cool Whip.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add shortening.
Mix as for pie dough.
Add milk and eggs as suggested.
Pat or roll 1/2 of dough onto cookie sheet.
Cover with 2 cans of cherries (sweetened to taste).
Cover cherries with remaining dough.
(May be latticed if desired.)
Cover top with 2 beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft.
Add turkey, half of the noodles, mushroom soup, soy sauce and milk or broth. Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with remaining noodles and cashews.
Bake at 350° until heated, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mystery blueberry pie
directions: Mash 1 cup blueberries.
In 2-quart saucepan, stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually, stir in water until smooth. Stir in the mashed blueberries and lemon rind.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Boil gently for 1 minute.
Pour into a bowl; cover with wax paper; cool.
Fold in remaining blueberries.
Whip cream.
Spread 1 1/2 cups cream over bottom and sides of pie shell.
Fill with blueberry mixture.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Chill until set (3 hours).

title: hemingway's trout
directions: Combine green onions, parsley, lemon juice and pepper.
Spread onion mixture in each trout cavity.
Spray trout on both sides with cooking spray, then coat with cornmeal.
Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a wide nonstick frying pan.
Add half of the fish and cook over medium heat, turning once, until fish is lightly browned and flakes easily when prodded in thickest portion.
For a 1-inch thick fish, allow 5 minutes on each side.
Cook remaining fish, using remaining oil, if necessary.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian love cake
directions: Make cake as directed on cake box.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, blend until smooth the Ricotta cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Pour this mixture over top of cake batter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Put all in crock-pot.
Add 1 cup cheese to top.
Cook on low for 3 hours.
Do not lift lid until done.

title: man friday curry
directions: Cut meat in 1/2 to 1-inch pieces (drain well).
In a big, heavy pot, put in oil and gently fry garlic, ginger and onions until soft and golden.
Add curry powder, salt and vinegar; mix well.
Then add diced meat and coat well with spices.
Add tomatoes, chillies and mint.
Cook until meat is tender.
Add garam marsala and cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cut cheese and margarine into small pieces and mix all together.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In
a
small
mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla
with
electric
mixer
at low speed.
Beat until smooth and
fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating at medium speed until nice and fluffy.

title: poor man's beef wellington
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and drain grease.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Mix both soups together with 1 cup milk. Cook until no longer lumpy.
Put 1 pie crust in pie dish.
Mix hamburger, broccoli and mushrooms with 1/2 of soup mixture.
Pour in crust and top with second pie crust.
Bake at 400° until pie crust is brown.
Use remaining soup as gravy on sliced wellington. Serves 8.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients. Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: baked italian potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes in a serving dish able to go from oven to table. Make mashed potatoes as you normally would using milk, butter and salt (if you use salt).
Try not to make them over mushy or lumpy; add a dash of garlic powder while mashing.
Mix in (not with electric mixer) most of the shredded Mozzarella.
You can shred and add more cheese if you love Mozzarella.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and add most of the breadcrumbs to the butter.
Pour over top of mashed potato mixture and smooth out with spoon.
Sprinkle remainder of shredded Mozzarella and then remainder of dry breadcrumbs over top.
Cover with foil and bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick chocolate custard
directions: Place 1 tablespoon coconut in each of four 6 ounce custard cups.
Combine chocolate pieces, evaporated milk and water in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until well blended.
Slowly stir in chocolate mixtures, blending well.
Pour into custard cups.
Place custard cups in 10-inch skillet and pour boiling water around cups to custard level.
Bring water to full rolling boil.
Cover skillet and simmer for 5 minutes.
Let custard set about 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl (except pie crust).
Mix well.
Follow directions on pie crust and then put mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 425 degrees for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean. You may want to put a cookie sheet under pies while cooking.

title: marlene's meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large bowl.
Shape mixture into a loaf and place in a greased loaf pan or baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Take loaf out of oven and place cheese slices on top.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in lightly salted water until tender.
Drain, mash and add cheese and finely chopped pepper and canned milk. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate almond pie
directions: Melt chocolate and marshmallows in milk in double boiler. Cool and when mixture begins to thicken, fold in whipped cream. Pour mixture into graham cracker crust (8-inch) and chill until firm.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in cast-iron pan.
Then add the kidney beans and tomato soup and put in chili powder, salt and pepper.
Put in water and cook over medium heat.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, salt, soup, cheese, 1/2 c. butter, pepper, onion, and sour cream.
Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Combine crushed corn flakes and the remaining 1/2 c. butter.
Spread on top of potatoes and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit for salad, mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Add pie mix.
Chill (overnight is better).
Before serving, add melon balls, bananas or strawberries.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; add water.
Boil until turns color.
Add egg yolk.
Cook 6 minutes.
Add butter, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Cool.
Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Add shrimp and toss to cover. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: ask-for-seconds cake
directions: Place margarine, raw quick oats and the boiling water in a bowl. Stir once or twice and set aside for 20 minutes.
Combine sugar, brown sugar, eggs, flour, salt, soda, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Thoroughly blend the oat mixture with the other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: casserole scallops
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with butter.
Arrange alternate layers of cracker crumbs and scallops in a 9-inch pie tin or flat casserole, making 3 layers of crumbs and two layers of scallops.
Pour the cream over the top, dut with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake in hot (425°) oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: grandma hornig's (madge) scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients and work in shortening with a pastry blender.
Add syrup and buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a floured surface; flip around a few times, then flatten out into a circle about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 8 wedges (a pizza cutter works great).
Put on a slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top will be only slightly brown.
Recipe may be doubled to make 16 at one time.

title: chess pie(2 deep crust pies)
directions: Mix sugar, butter and flour.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavor and milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake.

title: bar-b-q hamburgers
directions: Mix together and form into patties and brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets in 1 tablespoon salt. When cooked, peel and dice.
Add chopped onion and mix with sauce made in the following manner:
Cut bacon in small pieces and fry.
Add flour, sugar, butter, salt, pepper, vinegar and water. Bring to a boil, it will thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add cream and mix with potatoes.
Serves 10.

title: slaw
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve in 20 minutes.

title: peaches n' cream pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes. Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate. Drain peaches and reserve juice.
Place peaches over the batter in the plate.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved juice until smooth. Spoon to within 1-inch of edge of batter. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Place half of stuffing in bottom of casserole, then a layer of squash, then a layer of carrots, then a layer of onion. Blend sour cream, cream of chicken soup and milk.
Pour over top of casserole.
Put other half of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top the last 5 minutes.

title: supreme chicken casserole
directions: Cut into bite size pieces. Mix chicken with chestnuts, soup, celery, onion and sour cream together. Cover bottom of buttered casserole with 1/2 crushed cracker crumbs. Add chicken mixture and top with remaining crumbs. Dot with butter and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: rug deodorizer
directions: Mix 1 part water to 1 part vinegar in a spray bottle.
If unusual streaking occurs first time, it's due to the wax that some commercial cleaners contain.
Remove wax with a little rubbing alcohol and then clean with solution.

title: barbecue kielbasa
directions: Heat the grape jelly and chili sauce over medium heat until well blended.
Add the kielbasa.
Put the mixture into a crock-pot and cook for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit and 1
cup
sugar
in boiler and warm, do not boil, but melt good.
Put
butter
in 3 quart Pyrex dish.
Set in oven and melt.
Sift
flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt together;
add milk.
Pour batter in butter, put fruit on top and bake at 350° until crust is brown, about 1 hour.

title: german-style spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until barely done.
Heat margarine, onions and knockwurst in skillet and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in the soup, beer, sour cream, mustard and caraway seed.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Layer this mixture with spaghetti in a 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rock candy
directions: Sift powdered sugar over table (cover table well).
Boil sugar, water and syrup to 310° (hard crack).
Take off heat and add flavoring and coloring.
Stir quickly because candy will harden quickly after removed from heat.
Pour over powdered sugar. Cool and break.

title: quick vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and
serve with carrots, celery, zucchini, peppers, etc.

title: make-ahead hamburger mix
directions: Cook and stir meat and onion until meat is brown; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling, stirring frequently. Remove heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Divide among five (1-pint) freezer containers and freeze.

title: cube steak casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large skillet, heat 1/2-inch oil over medium heat. Flour cubed steak and brown on both sides about 3 minutes each side. Place cubed steak in baking dish.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In colander, mix zucchini and salt.
Let drain about 15 minutes, squeezing out excess liquid with back of spoon.
Mix well drained zucchini (about 1 cup) with remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into 1/2-inch hot oil in skillet and fry until brown on both sides.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot.
Makes about 12.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix water, sugar and margarine and bring to a boil.
Pour over dumplings that have been placed in baking dish.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add milk combining with oatmeal and raisins.
Mix well.
Add flour sifted with salt, soda and cinnamon.
Beat thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: pineapple angel food trifle
directions: Combine instant pudding mix with (save 1/2 cup) pineapple juice and milk in a large bowl.
Beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in pineapple tidbits and yogurt.
Place 1/3 of cake cubes in bottom of 16-cup glass bowl.
Drizzle with 3 tablespoons pineapple juice. Spoon 1/3 pudding mixture over this; repeat, ending with pudding mixture.
Cover and chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Cut suet into tiny pieces and melt in a 9 X 13 inch glass baking dish.
Take out cracklings.
Add broth from roast.
Mix rest of ingredients, pour over suet (and broth).
Do not stir. Bake 10 minutes at 400 degrees, then 15 minutes at 300 degrees.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Marinate chicken pieces in mixture 4 to 6 hours or overnight. Cook as usual on grill.

title: sweet 'n sour vegetables with chicken
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Stir-fry chicken; remove. Stir-fry onions and carrot.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill until set (3 hours).
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 - 9 inch pie.

title: beef stroganoff and noodles
directions: Dip meat in flour.
Brown and saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat. Simmer 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender; drain and set aside.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper, onion and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted.
Mix sauce with macaroni.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until bubbly and browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate sparkles
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Mix in other ingredients and blend well. Chill dough. Shape stiff dough into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Roll the balls in 1/4 cup sugar and place about 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on paper.
Store covered.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix all but the last 3 ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in a small mixing bowl until foamy.
Gradually add 8 tablespoons sugar, beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue onto hot pie filling, carefully sealing meringue to edge of crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool to room temperature.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer for 20 minutes.
I use this over my canned chevon or brown my ground chevon first, then drain and put sauce on.
Makes a delicious meat sandwich.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Clean cauliflower and cut in small pieces.
Fry bacon and drain off fat.
In bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
In large bowl, combine your cauliflower and bacon.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over cauliflower and mix.
Best if made the night before.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Add chopped onions, peppers, bay leaves and garlic.
Cook a few minutes.
Add canned tomatoes (chopped) and simmer 20 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Remain cooking 40 more minutes!

title: down-east biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients (except thyme).
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Mix just until dough almost forms.
Use hands and gently form soft dough.
You may have a little extra dry ingredients in bowl.
Pat into 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut into 2 1/2 inch rounds.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush top with butter and sprinkle with thyme.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Season with garlic salt.
Put all vegetables in casserole dish.
Add hamburger.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. After 40 minutes, add cheese and finish up baking.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix together with fork until like a ball. Turn onto lightly-floured board. Knead a few times. Roll out and cut into 1/2-inch strips. Melt 1 stick of butter and pour on cookie sheet. Roll strips in butter. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Turn over halfway. Can sprinkle with garlic salt.

title: mom's sunshine pickles
directions: Combine ingredients. Bring to a boil and boil until cukes are tender and clear (approximately 1/2 hour).
Pack at once in jars and seal.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Blend in all other ingredients and chill thoroughly.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Boil pineapple for 5 minutes.
Stir in Jell-O and nuts.
Let thicken in refrigerator.
Stir in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.

title: orange vegetable soup
directions: In large soup pan, combine cubed sirloin steak and Lipton onion
soup mix, cover with water, cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Add frozen vegetables, zucchini and tomato sauce special with bits.
Cut orange in half.
Take one half.
Grate 2 to 4 tablespoons rind and squeeze out juice.
Add grated rind and juice to soup.
Take other orange half.
Peel and cut into sections. Add to soup.
Cook for several hours.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar before serving.

title: big chocolate chip cookie in pizza pan
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until well blended.
Gradually beat in flour, baking soda and salt until well mixed.
Fold in chocolate morsels and nuts.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Press crescent rolls in bottom of pizza pan.
Layer with sausage, potatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and pepper and pour on top.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk; add crackers and vanilla. Chop fruits, add fruit, nuts and lemon peel to marshmallow mixture. Pack in cracker box; let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Slice and serve as needed.
Will keep in refrigerator for several months.

title: sausage-cheese dish
directions: Mix; roll into balls and bake at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes for 10 minutes.
While potatoes are boiling, melt butter.
Add salt, pepper and milk; bring to boil to thicken. Stir in mustard, onion and tuna.
Place in casserole dish.
Layer the potatoes, then the tuna mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts with bacon dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Add water, sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Fry bacon; remove from pan.
Save 4 tablespoons fat. Slowly add egg mixture to fat and stir until thickened.
Pour dressing over cooked Brussels sprouts and garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: cheesy corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour and milk.
Simmer until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat; add cheese. Stir until melted.
Combine corn, eggs, cheese sauce and seasonings in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Line bottom of medium casserole dish with stuffing.
Pour squash mixture over stuffing and spread more stuffing on top.
Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broiled sandwiches
directions: Heat all ingredients in double boiler.
Spread on hamburger buns and broil until hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Salt and pepper pork chops.
In oblong baking dish layer ingredients as follows:

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and bake in unbaked pie shell in 350° oven for 45 minutes and 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stalks and chop finely.
Place the mushrooms on a lightly buttered baking tray.
Put the chopped stalks in a bowl and add breadcrumbs, onion, garlic, parsley, anchovies and 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Add a small beaten egg.
Add pepper to taste.
Pile equal amounts onto the mushrooms; spoon the remaining oil over each.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and water chestnuts.
Cut onions into 1/2-inch rings.
Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Put slivered almonds on top.
Use pimento, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender until well blended.
Serve with apple slices.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: You need a 2-quart stock pot.
Put chicken in; fill with water.
Let cook 1 hour.
Slice celery; peel carrots and slice. Chop onion.
Take chicken out; let cool.
Put chicken, carrots, chicken bouillon, celery and onion in pot of broth; let cook 1 hour.
Cook noodles in separate pot; drain.
Put noodles in. It's ready to go.
Feeds about 10 people.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine beaten egg and milk.
Add flour and sugar and mix well. Let set 30 minutes.
Then stir in onion rings.
Lift out of batter and fry until brown.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat together the cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and cornstarch until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Take out 1 cup of batter and set aside.
In a separate bowl, stir together cocoa and remaining 1/4 cup sugar, then pour into batter.
Drop into main batter.
Swirl with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: quick & easy chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in a 9x13 baking dish and coat with Italian dressing.
(If time, marinade chicken 2 hrs. prior-but not necessary.)
Place in a 350° oven for 10 minute. then add layer of the diced tomatoes.
Sprinkle basil over the tomatoes.
Then coat with layer of bread crumbs and finally coat with layer of parmesan cheese.
Place back into the 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve over your favorite kind of cooked pasta.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Shape dough into balls, using rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Upon removing cookies from oven, immediately top each with a candy kiss.
Press down so cookie cracks around edge.

title: garbanzo bean and mixed vegetable salad(makes 6 cups; double for a crowd)
directions: Toss first 6 ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: cornish game hens(with rice and mushroom stuffing)
directions: Salt
and
pepper hens inside and out.	In small saucepan, cook
almonds,
onion
and	rice
in
butter for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring
often.
Add
water,
bouillon
cube, lemon juice	and salt.
Bring mixture to boil, stirring to dissolve bouillon
cube. Reduce
heat; cover and cook slowly for 20 to 25
minutes	or until
liquid is absorbed and rice is fluffy. Stir	in
drained mushrooms.	Lightly
stuff	birds with rice mixture.
Place breast
up	on
rack
in
shallow baking pan. Brush
with
melted butter.
Roast covered in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover
and roast for 1 hour longer or until drumstick	can
be
twisted easily
in	socket.
Brush birds with melted butter during last 15 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together (crust is flakier, the less you handle it).
Roll out on floured board and place in ungreased pie plates.
(Makes 1 double crust.)

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift dry ingredients (set aside).
Combine shortening and sugar; cream well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Mix well.
Shape into balls, using level tablespoon for each.
Roll each ball into crushed corn flakes.
Put 1/4 maraschino cherry on top of each.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 cup coconut, water and egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed of mixer.
Reduce speed for 1 minute. Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Cool cake in pan 10 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with toothpicks.
Pour cream of coconut over cake while warm. Cool.
Spread whipped topping over cake.
Sprinkle with coconut. Let chill at least 4 hours.

title: cranberry fruit nut bread
directions: Mix together by hand flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in 2 tablespoons shortening or margarine until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Combine orange juice, orange rind and egg.
Pour all at once into dry ingredients, mixing just enough to dampen.
Carefully fold in nuts and cranberries.
Spoon into greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Spread corners and sides slightly higher than center.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until crust is golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Place on cooling rack, top side up.

title: kool-aid playdough
directions: Mix together ingredients.
When cool enough to handle, knead the dough until it reaches the desired consistency, adding additional flour if needed.
Store in a plastic bag or airtight container.

title: slumber party peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
If you want, roll them into finely chopped, unsalted peanuts (they taste like Payday bars),
or roll into mini chocolate chips!

title: butterscotch chip pudding cookies
directions: Beat together margarine, eggs, sugar and brown sugar. Beat well, then add all dry ingredients.
Add chips last.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: onion bread
directions: Combine soup mix and butter.
Slice bread almost through. Spread butter on one side of each slice.
Wrap loaves in aluminum foil.
Heat at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the brown sugar, margarine, egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir in the flour and salt.
Press in greased oblong pan (9 x 13 x 2-inches).
Bake until light brown, 25 to 30 minutes. Place separated pieces of chocolate candy on crust.
Let stand until soft, spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into bars about 2 x 1/2-inches while warm.
Serves 32.
I love to munch!

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Add pineapple and pie filling.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and let gel.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet. Season with pepper, garlic salt, light chili powder, add white rice and water. Use directions on rice as to rice/water ratio- desired amount. Add one can Mexican stewed tomatoes, chopped green and red bell pepper, onions, chopped olives, and light chili powder. Put lid on skillet until rice is tender. Add Cheddar cheese and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stir together chicken, vegetables and soup.
Divide mixture between two of the pie shells.
Cover pies with the remaining crusts and seal edges.
Bake at 375° until crust is golden brown.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat together cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside cream mixture. In another bowl, sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add the water, cooking oil, vinegar and vanilla. Beat well.
The cocoa mixture will be thin.
Fill cupcake liners half full with cocoa mixture.
Drop 1 heaping tablespoon of cream cheese mixture on top of each cocoa mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil and add jello, water and lemon juice.
Place in refrigerator and let it set.
(Soft set.) Then add cheese, nuts and cool whip.
Return to refrigerator until set.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: grilled salmon with sherry vinegar honey glaze
directions: In a small saucepan, reduce the vinegar to 1/4 cup.
In a mixing bowl, combine vinegar syrup with mustard, honey and chili powder.
Let rest 30 minutes.
Preheat grill.
Brush salmon with glaze and grill 3 minutes per side for medium.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in water until tender.
Remove from water and drain.
Add salt and oleo and cream together.
Add cheese, egg, onion, milk and 1/2 cup of crumbs.
Put in a buttered baking dish and sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: pizza dough
directions: Scald milk.
Add margarine, salt and sugar.
Stir, and when cool, add egg; mix.
Add yeast and flour.
Add more flour and mix until dough is not sticky.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Mix together milk, margarine, sugar and salt.
Set aside to cool.
When this is cooled, mix with rest of ingredients.
Let stand 1/2 hour in very warm place.
Make into rolls.
Let rise for another 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pasti(german meat and potato pie)
directions: Spray bottom of a 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Line with pie shell. Layer potatoes on bottom of pie shell, then beef, onions, salt and pepper.
Continue layers, ending with potatoes.
Top with remaining pie shell.
Place 3 "air" slits on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Tasty with ketchup.)

title: butter cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter, then add vanilla flavoring and flour.
Fold whipping cream in dough.
Do not stir whipping cream in; fold in.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: one pot friccasse chicken
directions: Rinse and pat dry chicken.
Cut into halves.
Brown chicken to almost done.
Put aside.
Cut up all vegetables in little chunks. Cook in oil until almost brown.
Add about 1 cup water; stir around frequently.
Add chicken with all veggies in pot.
Add cream of chicken soup with another cup of water.
Let simmer on low heat until chicken is well done.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat together 2/3 cup reserved cake mix, brown sugar, white Karo syrup, vanilla and eggs. Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Return to 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: skillet macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat butter, uncooked macaroni and next 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Stir in water and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and cook over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 8 ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine corn flakes with melted butter; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: chicken a la grey poupon
directions: Combine mustard, wine, garlic, salt and pepper and brush on the chicken.
Place chicken in roasting pan.
Drizzle 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine over chicken.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour. Baste with juices.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in a 2-quart baking dish and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: woodford pudding
directions: Mix in order; bake at 375° or 400° for 30 minutes.

title: italian style chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Wash chicken parts.
Dry on paper towel. Put tomato juice in baking dish.
Roll chicken in juice, leaving the chicken skin side down.
Sprinkle spices over chicken.
Bake one hour in 350° oven.
Turn chicken over; add bamboo shoots. Bake 30 more minutes.

title: popsicles
directions: Kool-Aid and jello should be same flavor.
Dissolve Kool-Aid, jello and sugar in hot water.
Add cold water.
Makes 2 quarts liquid.
Takes about 6 hours to set.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix the ingredients and store in a jar in refrigerator. Marinate your favorite meats, (steaks, hamburger or chicken) with this delicious recipe for about 2 to 3 hours.
Bake chicken for 1 hour in a 350° oven or barbecue.

title: carolyn's chocolate fudge icing
directions: Ten minutes before cake is done, combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Mix and boil for 1 minute and remove from heat. Add chocolate chips (you can also use peanut butter or butterscotch chips instead of the chocolate ones.
You can also add nuts or a couple spoonfuls or peanut butter to mix in). Spread on cake just out of the oven while it is still hot!!! Spread on cake from the pan, small amount at a time.
Do not dump on cake and spread around because icing is heavy.
It is just like fudge.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Combine flour, butter and cream cheese in a bowl.
Rub with fingers until coarse crumbs form.
Add egg.
Stir with a fork until dough holds together.
Pat into a ball.
Roll out into pie pan. Fill with desired filling:
ground beef and tomatoes, quiche, etc. Bake at 425° for at least 30 minutes (relative to the filling). Can be chilled airtight up to 3 days.
Makes one 9-inch pie shell. Makes six servings.
Prep Time:
10 minutes.

title: peanut butter and cream cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine crackers and peanut butter; beat with electric mixer until combined.
Add powdered sugar and milk; beat until combined.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill in freezer 15 minutes.

title: stollen
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan, add milk, eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Transfer to a large bowl.
In 1/2 cup lukewarm water with 1 teaspoon sugar, dissolve yeast and wait 3 to 5 minutes until it bubbles.
Add 4 cups of flour and the yeast mixture to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour, cardamon and lemon peel. Beat vigorously for 10 to 15 minutes until very smooth and elastic.
Add nuts, raisins and currants, knead them into stollen while in bowl.
Cover and let rise until double, 2 to 4 hours. After rising, punch down.

title: mini hot rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Put batter in bite-size mini muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: my favorite snack - crisp fruit bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl blend together flour, oats, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Stir in Shedd's spread.
Using pastry blender or fingertips, work it like pastry to form a crumbly mixture.
Spread half the mixture in an even layer over bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Do not press down on it.
Spoon fruit over crust to form an even layer.
Scatter remaining mixture evenly over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: toffee sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil rapidly for 3 minutes.
Serve warm on ice cream or plain cake. Makes about 2 cups.

title: best dip
directions: Cut circle on top of bread and pick bread out so that it is hollow, except for a thick wall to hold dip.
Mix all ingredients together; bake for 1 hour at 360°.
Wrap in tinfoil and serve warm.
This will be a big success.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Roll in chopped pecans. Chill.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir into apples.
Turn into pastry shell.
Combine remaining flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: sue tysor's blender sweet potato or fresh pumpkin pie filling
directions: Place all ingredients in electric blender in order given.
Be sure to drain potatoes or pumpkin well.
Blend on high until creamy like a milk shake.
Fills one uncooked deep dish pie shell. Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Bake 35 minutes longer at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Tastes best when served cold.

title: curried tuna salad in pita bread
directions: Stir together the yogurt, mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice and chutney.
Add the tuna and mix well.
Stir in the nuts.
Fill the pitas with the tuna salad; tuck the lettuce and tomato into the pita pocket and serve.
Makes four servings.

title: golden cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and onion in 2 quarts of chicken broth until tender.
Add broccoli-cauliflower and soup.
Cook about 5 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Make batter with first 6 ingredients.
Pour batter over peaches. Mix 1 cup sugar and cornstarch and sprinkle over batter. Pour boiling water over all. Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Chill first 3 ingredients until slightly thickened.
Add cranberry sauce.
Freeze in mold.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine.
Then add other ingredients. Cook at 250° until light brown for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pizzelle(waffle cookies)
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar until light and fluffy or foamy.
Add shortening or oil a little at a time.
Add the flavorings and grated rind into this.
Gradually blend about 4 cups of flour to make a thin dough.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix liquids together, fat last. Use pan, skillet or muffin pan.
Bake in oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 24 pieces.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Place bread cubes in one-quart baking dish.
Pour butter over and toss to coat.
Mix Hunt's tomatoes with brown sugar, salt and basil and pour over the bread cubes; stir.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Trim any excess fat from pork; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Dust with flour.
In saucepan, brown pork in shortening.
Add mushroom gravy, onion, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cover; cook over low heat 30 minutes, stirring now and then.
Add green pepper and pineapple.
Cover; cook over low heat 15 minutes or until pork and green peppers are tender.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix margarine and garlic powder and brush over hot biscuits.

title: macaroni hot dish
directions: Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish or larger. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla, Karo and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 1 hour in a 300° oven.
Cover with foil the first 20 minutes.

title: peach jello pie
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until thickened, then add 1 package peach jello. Stir in fresh peaches. Chill slightly.
Pour into a baked pie shell. Top with Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Add the peanut butter and stir in marshmallows.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Cut into small pieces.

title: quickies
directions: Melt butter.
Dip each biscuit in melted butter.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and sugar and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix and set in fridge. Mix jello, boiling water and strawberries.
If berries are very juicy, remove water.
Let set until begin to jell.
Next, put cheese mixture in crust.
Put jello mixture on top.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts (pecans or walnuts).

title: white chocolate chips brownies(very rich and moist)
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Over medium heat, stirring constantly, bring sugar, butter and water to a boil.
Turn off heat.
Mix in vanilla and semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Stir until chocolate is melted and mixture smooth.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Let mixture cool 15 minutes (very important to cool).
Mix in white or milk chocolate pieces.

title: date-nut refrigerator bran muffins
directions: In medium bowl, pour water over 2 cups cereal; allow mixture to cool.
In a large bowl, blend sugar, oil, eggs and buttermilk; stir in dry and soaked cereal.
Add in dry ingredients, then dates and nuts.
Batter can be baked immediately or refrigerated in a tightly covered container up to 1 month.
Use paper muffin cup liners. Spoon batter into muffin cup; allow to stand in pans while the oven heats.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Makes about 60 muffins.

title: white frosting
directions: Mix flour with milk, cook until it forms a paste, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream shortening, butter, sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Add cooled paste and beat for about 5 minutes.

title: hollander cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening together.
Add eggs, vanilla and warm water to creamed mixture; blend well.
Add flour, baking soda and baking powder, which have been sifted together.
Combine oatmeal, coconut and nuts together; add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes, or until done.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour until it resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk; blend with fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead 4 to 6 strokes.
Roll into a 14 x 20-inch rectangle.
Spread butter over dough, leaving a narrow margin on all sides.
Combine sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over dough.
Add nuts and raisins, if desired. Beginning at long side of dough, roll up in jelly roll fashion. Pinch ends and edge to seal; cut roll into 1-inch slices.
Place slices, cut side down, in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: dunking platters
directions: Mix butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder and stir in.
In the following order, stir in oatmeal, coconut, raisins and cornflakes.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about nine dozen.
Dunk in milk or coffee and enjoy.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter; place in bottom, of prebaked pastry shell.
Add cheese (you may substitute Cheddar or Swiss).
Beat eggs until frothy with electric mixer; gradually stir in milk.
Pour on top of cheese. Sprinkle bacon and parsley on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 15 minutes on a cookie sheet.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from mushrooms and chop stems fine.
Melt margarine in skillet and add chopped stems, parsley and onions; brown lightly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Dot tops with margarine and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Place mushrooms in shallow pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brush with margarine and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear or cut up lettuce and place in a large glass salad bowl. Layer remaining ingredients in order stated.
Make sure the mayonnaise seals the edges.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Bacon and tomatoes may be added just before serving.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mash graham crackers and mix with nuts, dates and cherries. Then melt marshmallows in milk and add to first mixture.
Line tube pan with wax paper and pack mixture in firmly a little at a time.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from pan and keep refrigerated.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown meat, breaking into small pieces.
Add garlic, onion and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes or until thick.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Makes approximately 8 burgers.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole dish pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Bake, covered, at 350°.

title: oreo pie
directions: Grease lightly a pie pan or cake pan.
Crush Oreos.
Place most crumbs in pan, saving some for topping.
Press firmly in bottom.
Spread ice cream on crumbs.
You may not need entire quart.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Slice.

title: flan
directions: Put condensed milk, milk, eggs, vanilla and cream cheese in a blender; blend until smooth.

title: beef broth
directions: Place all ingredients in 3-quart pot and bring to a boil. Partly cover pan and simmer for 1 hour.
Strain.
Chill and remove fat.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Beat egg yolks slightly.
Beat in milk, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Fold into beaten egg whites.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole dish. Place casserole in square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, on oven rack; pour very hot water (1 inch deep) into pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cool and, if desired, with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings; 195 calories per serving.

title: hot cocoa for a few
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Blend in water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it boils.
Add milk.
Stir and heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot.
Yields about 6 (6 ounce) servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and salt, alternating with flour.
Add vanilla.
Dissolve soda in hot water; mix with vinegar holding over bowl as it will foam. Quickly add mixture to batter.
Pour into three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and frost with a frosting for Red Velvet Cake.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight. Cook beans and pork in plenty of water in a cooker until they start to get soft, then put in crock-pot, pan or bean pot.
Mix the catsup, brown sugar and molasses. Stuff the onions in middle of the mixture and bake slowly 3 hours. Good for freezer.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk, egg yolks and lemon juice in a bowl.
Using a wire whip, mix together well.
It will thicken automatically.
Pour filling into shell. Place vanilla wafers around edge of filled pie, leaving approximately one-half of the wafer above the fill line.
Top pie with Cool Whip.
Cover pie with plastic wrap.
Place pie in freezer at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve frozen.

title: shawn's savory sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, olives, sour cream, green chilies, 1 package Monterey Jack cheese, Cheddar cheese, chicken and seasonings in large mixing bowl.
Butter one large baking pan.
Place about 2 tablespoonfuls of mixture onto each tortilla, roll up and place in pan.
Top with remaining mixture (if any) and Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is well melted at 325°.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Slightly heat tortillas.
Mix ingredients together.
Spread mixture over flour tortillas and roll into tight roll.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices and serve on garnish tray.

title: mondo crab cakes
directions: Gently mix in bowl; shape into patties. Fry until sides are golden brown. Serve with cocktail sauce (if you want) while hot.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix ingredients well and press into greased 10 x 8-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Cool.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball and refrigerate.

title: zucchini banana bread
directions: Slice bananas into blender.
Whirl until pureed.
Combine flours, wheat germ, sesame seed, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat in bananas until smooth.
Add flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in zucchini and add raisins.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 55 to 60 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to complete cooling.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: greater tater casserole
directions: Layer the ingredients in a baking dish in order given.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: southwest stew
directions: Brown beef and onions in a skillet; drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar and egg.
Add flour and soda.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Put in a greased and floured bread pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix
the first 3 ingredients with a fork until blended. Press in bottom
and
up
sides
of
a 9 x 13-inch pan (like a crust). Combine
powdered
sugar,
cream
cheese and eggs and beat with
a mixer
until
smooth.
Pour into pan with crust; top with pecans. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour, brown in butter and remove.
Stir soup, seasonings and water into drippings.
Cook and stir to a boil. Spread rice from box into a casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over rice and stir to moisten.
Top with chicken pieces.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: easy liver pate
directions: Bring sausage to room temperature.
Place egg, brandy, onion and seasonings in blender and whirl until well mixed.
Add drained, chopped livers and blend until smooth.
Add blender mixture to sausage, mix thoroughly and place in loaf pan.
Cover tight, with foil and place in larger pan with boiling water to come up halfway. Bake 1 3/4 to 2 hours.
Cool, drain and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Dip chicken in flour and egg. Brown in butter (about 4 minutes on each side).
Place chicken in baking dish and top each piece with small amount of spinach. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and put slice of Mozzarella cheese on each piece.
Bring chicken broth and wine to slow boil and add lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Good with fettucini.

title: onion rings
directions: To steam onions in large skillet or wok, bring 1-inch of water to a boil, position a steamer rack just above water.
Separate onion slices into rings and place on rack.
Cover and steam until rings are tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 2 large baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray.

title: hamburger lentil soup
directions: Brown hamburger in large pan.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil, then simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until lentils are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated shrimp salad
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Mix oil, ketchup, sugar, vinegar and onion together.
Pour over shell macaroni.
Marinate overnight.
Rinse and drain shrimp.
Add remaining ingredients.
Garnish with sliced eggs and larger shrimp.

title: party pink salad
directions: Drain
pineapple.
Combine
the juice, marshmallows and Jell-O and allow
to
dissolve
over low heat.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and	nuts. Whip the cream with sugar, then fold with Jell-O mixture.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix in order as given.
Use a large mixing bowl.
Bake in muffin pans 2/3 full 15 to 20 minutes.
This dough will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Use as needed.
Bake at 400°.

title: old-fashioned stew for two
directions: Place meat cubes in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add potato, carrot, celery and onion.
Combine water, browning sauce, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Tuck bay leaf into liquid.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap, stirring midway through cooking.
Microwave on High 5 minutes. Microwave on Medium-low (30%) 25 to 30 minutes . Stir and let set 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 2 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.
Use 3-quart casserole.
Double ingredients.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Also known as 7 layer dip.

title: fruit pies
directions: Fill the middle of each tortilla with a small amount of pie filling.
Fold ends over and then roll sides inward.
Secure with a wooden toothpick.
Brown in oil in skillet on both sides.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Rinse and drain.
Combine with all other ingredients except cheese.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Wash, rinse, drain and cut vegetables as wanted.
Dissolve salt in 1 gallon water.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand about 18 hours.
Drain.
Add seeds (also spices if wanted) and sugar to vinegar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Simmer until hot through, then bring to boiling.
Pack boiling hot into hot jar. Seal at once.

title: cherry pie
directions: Crust:
Mix together flour, shortening, sugar, chopped pecans and water.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine the cabbage, parsley and onion.
Put 2 tablespoons oil on this; let cool until ready to serve.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: italian cheese ball
directions: Combine dressing mix and cheese well into a ball.
May be served as a spread on rye bread.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; cool and drain.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard; beat again.
Add bread crusts; stir.
Add cheese, mushrooms and sausage; stir.
Put into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Great for the brunch bunch.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: asparagus fritters
directions: Drain asparagus and chop very fine.
Mix eggs, baking powder, flour, milk and salt.
Add asparagus.
Mix well.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pat butter on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Drain and set aside.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese and pepper.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown on top and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Season 3-quart shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
In medium bowl,
beat eggs. Gradually beat in sugar. Beat well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk; beat until creamy.
Fold in 2/3 of Cool Whip.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top of pie.
Serve after 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: penne with roasted asparagus, pine nuts and lemon
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place pine nuts in a baking pan and toast about 8 minutes.
Remove and increase oven to 450°.Cut asparagus tips at an angle.
Peel stalks and cut same size as tips.
Add oil, salt and pepper.
Roast on baking sheet in oven about 15 minutes, tossing several times.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Cook penne according to directions on package and drain.
Transfer pasta to large saute pan.
Add chicken stock and lemon juice.
Cook until liquid reduced about 5 minutes.
Add butter, 3/4 cheese, asparagus, salt and pepper and cook until butter melts.
Stir in herbs. Season sprinkled with pine nuts and remaining cheese.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt Crisco in a pan over low heat; let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Chill.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Should be soft and chewy.

title: easy dish ham bake
directions: Mix broccoli, cheese soup, mushroom soup and 1 cup milk; add ham, onion powder in ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 1/2-inch rectangular.
Mix Bisquick mix and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Mix cake per directions on box.
Set aside.
Beat first 7 ingredients at high speed until smooth and creamy and set aside. Grease a tube pan.
Pour half of cake batter into pan; pour cheese filling over cake batter and top with remaining cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cake rises very high and then drops a bit.
This may also be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.
When cool, spread with cream cheese frosting.

title: white bread
directions: Mix yeast with warm water until dissolved.
Add the rest of the ingredients, knead and let rise.
Shape into loaves and rise again.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions for 5 minutes in salt water; drain well.
Mix soup and sour cream in a mixing bowl; stir in carrots. Set aside.
Add squash and onions. In a pot, melt butter; add bread crumbs and seasonings.
Put 1/2 stuffing mix on bottom of casserole dish.
Pour sour cream mixture in.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake rum balls
directions: Optional:
Small chocolate chips, sunflower seeds, 2 tablespoons instant coffee, coconut, chocolate sprinkles, etc.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole.
In 1-quart saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in undiluted soup and cream cheese cubes, stirring constantly until smooth.
In casserole, alternate frozen potatoes and hot sauce, ending with sauce layer.
Cover and bake 45 minutes until sauce is bubbly. Remove and sprinkle with cheese.

title: hot sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Pour mixture into baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add Italian dressing.
Mix well with Salad Supreme seasoning.
Refrigerate or serve cold with crackers.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix together; sprinkle with 1/2 pound cooked, cut up bacon. Cover and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, peppers, salt, onions and pimientos and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain and rinse.
Mix the vinegar, pickling spice, turmeric, sugar and celery salt in a saucepan. Heat to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Remove spices; mix squash mixture in and boil for 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal. Makes about 6 to 61/2 pints.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Grease large Bundt or angel food pan.
Pour nuts into bottom of pan, evenly.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Arrange biscuits in pan, melt oleo and pour over biscuits.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger, sausage, onion and green pepper.
Add mustard, brown sugar, catsup to beans and stir.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scallop
directions: Layer potatoes and onions in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix butter, flour and milk together.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over potatoes and onions.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are done.
Can add leftover such as diced ham, smoked sausage, whole kernel corn, green peas or cooked carrots.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until
tender.
Combine other ingredients, except cracker crumbs,
with drained cabbage.
Sprinkle garlic salt on top and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles; add to other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish; top with another cup of grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt margarine; work in peanut butter and sugar and crushed graham crackers.
Roll in a roll and refrigerate until firm, then cut.
Spread melted chips over top.
Walnut or peanut halves can be put on top.
Refrigerate until set.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Prepare vegetables before heating wok.
Slice vegetables diagonally.
Separate broccoli into small flowerets.
Spray wok with cooking spray.
Use paper towel to spread evenly over wok. Heat wok to medium-high.
Put beef in wok, a few pieces at a time. Brown on all sides.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with soy sauce; set aside.
Add sherry to wok; blend to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until vegetables are crisp-tender (about 7 minutes).
Serve alone or with white rice. Yield:
3 to 4 servings.

title: peas with water chestnuts
directions: Simmer peas and water chestnuts in chicken broth, about 5 minutes or until peas are done.
Add butter and seasonings, if desired.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in casserole dish for 15 minutes, until bubbly in 350° oven.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese. Bring to boil over medium heat; cover and let stand 10 minutes. Tossing with fork, place a layer of rice mixture in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Add a layer of chicken; repeat layers, adding cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in pecans. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Cool in pan. Cream together cream cheese and sugar. Fold Cool Whip into cream cheese mixture. Pour over cooled crust. Mix sliced strawberries and glaze. Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: vegetable cheese cazuela(serves 8)
directions: In saucepan, combine tomato sauce, taco sauce, taco seasoning and water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
In small bowl, combine sour cream and cottage cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Drain.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs and cheese.
In buttered 2-quart casserole, layer bread crumbs, squash and cheese.
Repeat and top with remaining bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and place in a bowl.
Add butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese; mix well. Spread over the bottom and up the sides of a greased 10-inch deep-dish pie plate.
Spoon cottage cheese on top of the spaghetti; set aside.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make a thick batter.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Great with fried fish.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Place berries in an 8 x 11.5-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
Mix sugars, cinnamon and flour together.
Add sugar mixture to berries. Cut margarine up into small pieces and place on top of berries. Top with your favorite pie crust or frozen crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, chocolate, sweetener and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 8-inch square baking pan lined with foil.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 16 squares.
Serve chilled.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix cake mix and margarine together.
Press 3/4 of mix into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Set leftover cake mixture aside.

title: chicken in rice fiesta salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, chilies, lemon juice, chili powder and salt; mix well.
Add rice and chicken; mix well.
Cover and chill. Serve on lettuce covered platter.
Top with tomatoes, avocados, olives and chips.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put 1 stick margarine in deep baking dish and set in oven to melt.
Make batter of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour batter over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Put fruit over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake for 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in flour, blending well.
Stir in vanilla, morsels and pecans.
Spoon batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool; cut into squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs; add to shortening and sugar.
Press bananas through a sieve and add along with lemon juice.
Blend into cream mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; mix into banana mixture. Add nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 (1 pound) loaf.

title: creamy mexican dip
directions: In a saucepan combine all ingredients. Cook until mixed well about 5 to 7 minutes. Put in bowl cover and chill.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Boil corned beef in seasonings as directed on bag until tender.
Let cool completely.
Spread dressing on each slice of bread.
Cover bread slice with thinly sliced corned beef, kraut, cheese and onion.
Place other slice on top with dressing facing sandwich filling.
Heat 1 tablespoon at a time of margarine in a nonstick skillet and brown sandwich on each side.
This will make 12 sandwiches.

title: hearty shaker soup
directions: Combine 1 cup broth, vermouth (if desired) and butter in small saucepan. Bring to a boil over high heat. Continue
to boil until liquid is reduced to 1/4 cup and has a syrupy consistency, about 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in cream. Set aside.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix until well blended.
(Food coloring may be added.)
Serve with fresh fruit or cookies as dippers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook on low for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until center is done when tested.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, onion, mustard and sauerkraut.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan:
sauerkraut mixture, corned beef, Swiss cheese and crumbled rye Melba toast.
Pour butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda. Let stand a few minutes. Cream butter, sugar. Add egg and beat. Add vanilla. Sift flour baking powder, salt and add with date mixture. Bake 350° about 25 minutes.

title: salad with romaine lettuce(quick and light)
directions: Tear romaine into bite-size pieces.
Place in salad bowl; cover and chill until ready to serve.
Combine remaining ingredients except tomatoes.
Let stand at room temperature about an hour to blend flavors.
Remove garlic before serving.
Toss romaine with just dressing to lightly coat.
Garnish with tomato slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: margarita pie
directions: Mix pretzels and butter and pat in 9-inch pie pan.
Blend sugar, milk, lemon juice and Triple Sec.
Fold in whipped cream. Cool in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight.

title: toasted onion canapes
directions: Set oven to broil or 550°.

title: quick rhubarb pie
directions: Beat sugar, egg and oil.
Add salt, soda, vanilla and milk. Mix in flour and blend well. Fold in rhubarb.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes in preheated oven.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter, add sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes stirring often.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: lemon fluff dessert(very easy to make; make the day before)
directions: Whip whipping cream and fold into milk and lemon mixture.
Line pie tin with vanilla wafers and pour mixture over it.
Crush two wafers and sprinkle on top.
Chill overnight.

title: no cook boiled custard
directions: Blend condensed milk and pudding with mixer.
Add cold milk, mixing well.
Set aside until thickened.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In a large saucepan, cook chicken in boiling water until done.
Drain, saving water.
Chop chicken into small pieces.
Add spaghetti to chicken water and cook until done, following directions on package.
In another pan, melt butter and saute celery and onion.
Stir in pimento.
Add chicken, soup, milk, Velveeta, salt and pepper.
Drain spaghetti and add to chicken mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Sprinkle cheddar on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: creamy-crunchy chicken
directions: Boil chicken in a small amount of water for 20 minutes.
Cool and remove chicken from bone (do not use skin).
In a bowl mix chicken, soups, sliced water chestnuts, water and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Crumble 1/2 box Escort crackers on bottom of a greased casserole dish; then place chicken mixture on crumbs. Crumble rest of Escort crackers on top of mixture.
Melt stick of oleo and pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: ambrosia
directions: Cut oranges first.
When peeling orange, hold over bowl so juice will remain in bowl.
Be sure to cut sections deep enough to remove all membrane from orange.
Remove sections by cutting along the side of each, dividing membrane from outside to center.

title: aztec chocolate
directions: Grate the unsweetened chocolate into a bowl and cover it with a little of the boiling water. Mash the mixture into a paste. Add the rest of the water and vanilla and beat with an electric mixer until frothy. Add the pepper and chilies to liven up the drink. The chocolate will not totally dissolve and will have a grittiness to it.

title: perfect divinity
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients using a candy thermometer.
When it gets to 250°, beat egg whites until forms stiff peaks.
Cook until 260° hard ball stage.
