Pour into egg whites, beating as you pour. Beat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drop by spoons on wax paper; top with a pecan.

title: mushroom roast
directions: Put roast in a crock-pot.
Add water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook as directed by crock-pot directions.
About 1 hour before you eat, add 2 cans of mushroom soup.
Stir in.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Combine candy, coffee and water in saucepan until candy is melted. When cooled, fold into Cool Whip and blend well.
Pour mixture into cooled pie crust.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, combine 1 1/2 cups cheese with the remaining ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup of the Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave about 10 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: open face burger bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook and stir ground beef, drain and set aside.
Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip, cheese and onions; set aside.
Stir Bisquick and water to soft dough.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Pat dough into pan, pressing 1/2-inch up sides of pan.
Layer beef and tomatoes on dough. Spoon sour cream mix over top.
Bake until edges are light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer 45 minutes.

title: smothered cabbage wedges
directions: Cook cabbage in small amount of salted water; drain well. Place cooked cabbage in baking dish.
In small saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper; add milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spoon cheese over wedges and bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with ground nutmeg.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, eggs and 3/4 cup sugar.
Put in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Leave cool for 15 minutes.
Beat together sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Pour on top of pie.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top with fruit of your choice.

title: tri-color pasta salad
directions: Make rotini as per box directions.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Re-toss before serving, if you let it sit for more than 30 minutes.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Make 4 hamburger patties and place on a piece of foil.
Top with a slice of onion.
Peel potatoes; cut in half and place on each side.
Clean carrots; cut in half and place on each end. Season to taste.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
Add a salad and you have a great meal.
Serves 4.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until tender, about 8 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add flour and stir 2 minutes.
Gradually add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add asparagus and summer savory and simmer until asparagus is tender, about 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and drain asparagus, reserving liquid.

title: hearty hamburger stew
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a heavy skillet.
Add onion and garlic and cook over low heat.
Stir in ground beef with a fork.
When meat is no longer red, add other ingredients.
Cook and cover over a low heat for about 30 minutes, or until carrots are tender.
Serve in deep bowl, topped with toasted French bread and sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from oven, let cool for 15 minutes and cut into squares.
Very good!
Tastes like pizza.

title: party casserole
directions: Brown meat, add onions, cook until tender. Stir in milk and cream cheese. Add corn, soup and pepper. Place noodles in casserole dish, top with ground beef mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Take cake mix and mix according to directions.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan and cool.
Cook flour and milk until thick.
Let cool. Beat together margarine, Crisco, sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Combine both mixtures and beat until fluffy and creamy.
Slice cake through middle long ways.
Spread filling and put other layer on top.
Cover and seal for 24 hours.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Combine soup mixtures and pour over sliced potatoes that fill a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add 1 cup of diced process cheese.
Mix well.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°, covered.
Remove cover during last 30 minutes of baking.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions on box. Pour into two 9 x 13 pans. Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°. While cakes are baking, combine 1 cup sugar and 1 cup evaporated milk in a saucepan. Bring to rapid boil; remove from heat and add the marshmallows. Stir until dissolved.

Add coconut and pour over one of the baked cakes. Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1 stick margarine and 1/2 cup evaporated milk; bring to a rapid boil. Remove from heat and stir in the chocolate chips. Stir until chips are melted; add about 1 cup of the chopped nuts. Mix well. Put other baked cake on top and pour chocolate mixture over it. Sprinkle remaining nuts on top of cake.

title: "granny's" sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Sift flour and soda and add alternately with sour cream.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: easy caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Place popped corn in a large roasting pan. Let it stay in oven while preparing glaze.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add broth and milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into bottom crust of pie plate, then cover with top crust and cut slits into crust.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: austrian sauerkraut
directions: Brown onion very well in grease; add sauerkraut and brown sugar.
Simmer, covered, about 20 to 25 minutes until almost dry. Especially good with sausage.

title: soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend dry ingredients and raisins. Warm milk and blend in honey or molasses until dissolved.
Add slowly to dry ingredients.
Knead the dough 3 to 4 minutes.
Form into a ball.
Place on flat pan and cut a shallow cross (+) on top of the bread.
Sprinkle about a tablespoon of milk on the bread before baking.
Bake at 400° for approximately 40 minutes until brown.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Boil and drain spaghetti according to box directions.
Mix milk and eggs.
Combine with spaghetti.
Put spaghetti in boiler pan.
Pour over jar of spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over spaghetti; add pepperoni.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes.

title: quick chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place dressing on bottom of baking dish.
Layer chicken on top of dressing.
Dilute soups and pour over chicken and dressing. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
May put onion rings on top 5 minutes before taking from oven.
Yields 8 servings.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans; put in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour on top of coconut and nuts.
Put butter and cream cheese in microwave to soften.
Mix box of sugar with butter and cream cheese, mix well. Spoon over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: beef stew
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown stew meat in 2 tablespoons oil. Add 2 tablespoons onion soup mix and stir well.
Add can of soup and 1/2 to 1 can of water and stir.
Peel potatoes and carrots and add to mixture along with mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch last 5 minutes, if desired.
Can be made in crock-pot, cooking it about 8 to 10 hours on low.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine brown sugar and cream/half and half. Add butter/margarine. Microwave on High 7 1/2 to 9 minutes, stirring once. Add pecans and let set for 1 minute. Stir mixture until it loses its shape, about 3 minutes. Drop onto waxed paper to let set.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steaks in strips and sprinkle with paprika; let stand. Then brown meat in large skillet with onions and butter.
Add garlic and broth and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in green peppers and cover.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Stir until thick and clear.
Add tomatoes and cook 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt, pepper and garlic salt in large skillet.
Add soups, tomatoes, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Line bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with taco flavored Doritos.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: fly off the plate rolls
directions: At the same time that yeast is soaking, put the following into a large bowl:
flour, salt, sugar, shortening and hot water.
Beat these together and let set until cooled to lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour to make stiff dough (about 7 cups).
Turn out and knead until smooth.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and make into roll or loaf.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes for rolls or 50 minutes for loaf.

title: graham cracker nut balls
directions: Starting with oleo and crackers, mix all but last 2 ingredients together with hands.
Make into small balls.
Melt chips with wax.
Dip balls.
You can roll in 10x sugar instead of chocolate chips.
You may also use butterscotch chips instead of chocolate chips.
For a variety, do some of each.

title: karen's cranberry ice
directions: Wash and drain cranberries; remove any stems.
Place in medium saucepan with 2 cups water.
Bring to boiling; boil for 6 to 8 minutes, or until soft, stirring frequently.
Press cranberries and liquid through sieve to puree; return to saucepan.
Stir sugar into cranberries.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and orange juice. Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Freeze 8 hours or overnight.
Cut into 16 squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetables. Chill mixture for a few hours or more before serving.
Always serve chilled.

title: angel cake
directions: Get a birthday cake pan.
Rip or cut cake into pieces.
Put into bottom of cake pan.
Make instant vanilla pudding.
Pour over angel cake.
Take strawberries; clean, cut into pieces (throw green parts away).
Spread cut strawberries on the pudding cake. Cake requires no refrigeration; you can eat that day or put in refrigerator for tomorrow.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating until well blended.
Add all 6 eggs and blend well.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to egg mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soups, milk, and water.
Place in lightly greased 9x13 baking dish.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle with dried onion soup mix. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1-1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chocolate cups
directions: You will also need cupcake holders.

title: crab cakes
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in flour to make smooth mixture.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring, reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Beat some hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to rest of mixture in saucepan.
Cook, stirring, several minutes until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Drain crabmeat.

title: raspberry cream cheese baked french toast
directions: In a 9 x 13 inch greased dish or pan, place half of slices of bread to cover bottom.
(Or cube bread to cover bottom.)
Add berries to cover bread.
Spread all of the cream cheese on what will be the top layer of bread (or dab onto bread cubes).
If bread is whole, spread bread with cream cheese and place, cream side down, onto berries.
If bread is cubed, spread the bread on top of cream cheese layer.
Mix all liquid ingredients and pour over bread mixture so it covers top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning preheat oven to 350°.
Mix topping ingredients and spread over top of layered French toast.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes (cover during first half of baking).
Top will be slightly browned and kind of crusty when done.
Cut into squares, place on large plate and serve topped with maple syrup and or yogurt.
Makes 8 servings.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet; cover tightly and cook only 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut up all ingredients.
Use Hidden Valley dressing mix (without buttermilk).
Mix it as directed.
Put dressing over salad when ready to serve.
Salad is better if let set overnight.

title: coke chicken
directions: Place drumsticks in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and lay sliced onion over chicken.
Pour ketchup and then Coke. Simmer in skillet 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
If you don't like ketchup or Coke, you may substitute a bottle of dry sherry!

title: doug's pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly brown pork chops in skillet; set aside.
Thinly slice potatoes and onions.
Tear off 4 large sheets of aluminum foil and place 1 pork chop and 1 ear of corn in each, along with a sliced potato and sliced onion (place onions on pork chop).
Lightly sprinkle with dill weed and place 1 pat of butter or margarine on top of onions.
Tightly seal foil and place in oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: no fail cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream first four ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Mix well.
At low speed, add flour gradually.
Add flavoring.
Do not overbeat.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Allow to cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: stir-fried chicken fajitas
directions: In a heavy plastic bag, combine chicken strips and dressing; refrigerate for several hours, turning bag occasionally.
Drain.

title: boiled shrimp in hull
directions: Add all ingredients to water except shrimp; bring to a boil. Add washed shrimp.
Cover.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer for 3 to 5 minutes, depending on size.
Remove from heat and let stand 3 more minutes.
Drain and chill.
Can be hulled and deveined or served in shell.
Good with catsup base cocktail sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine peaches, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
On a floured surface, roll half the pastry into 12-inch circle.
Fit into a 9-inch pie plate, leaving a 10-inch circle.
With a sharp knife, cut pastry into 3/4-inch wide strips.
Carefully arrange strips on fruit, 1 inch apart, in a lattice pattern; trim edge.
Bake 1 hour or until filling is bubbly.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Empty pie filling into dish.
Pour crushed pineapple over filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple and pour melted margarine.
Then sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until coconut is browned.

title: mushroom turnovers
directions: Saute onions in butter until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in and cook gently the thyme, salt, flour, sour cream and black pepper.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: mosy salad
directions: Bring to a boil and add a 3 ounce package of raspberry jello.

title: very easy dumplings
directions: Combine flour and beaten egg, shortening, salt and water.
Mix until dough is soft.
Roll out thin.
Cut into small strips and drop in boiling broth.
Cook until tender.

title: cocoa fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Sift flour, cocoa, sugar, salt and soda together in large bowl.
Add vanilla, vinegar, oil and water; beat into dry ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Allow to cool and ice in pan with cocoa frosting.
Serves 24.

title: date balls
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in saucepan on medium heat.
Stir constantly for 10 minutes or until it boils.
Remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups Rice Krispies, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts; mix well.
Roll into balls (grease hands or use spoon) and drop into coconut.
Roll to coat. Store in airtight container.
(Freezes well.)

title: lemon-coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine flour, soda and baking powder.
Alternate flour and milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 325°.

title: chocolate chewy squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in well-greased 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned soft gingerbread
directions: Blend all ingredients, except flour.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and blend.
Then add the remaining cup of flour.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until center is done.
Delicious served warm.

title: ruth clapper's shortcake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix with egg and milk.
Do not beat.
Bake in a lightly greased pin tin at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Watch carefully, so not to overbrown.
Test with a straw. Cut into pie-shaped servings.
Split each while hot.
Butter same. Serve with topping of sugared strawberries or other desired fruit.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Blend cake mix, oil and margarine in large mixer bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, with mixer; then beat according to directions on cake mix box.
Fold in sour cream and nuts.
Pour half the batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Sprinkle sugar-cinnamon mixture evenly over the batter.
Pour remaining batter in pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until it tests done at 350°.
Remove from the oven and cook in pan for 5 minutes. Turn out on cake plate and pour on milk glaze while cake is still warm.

title: sauce vinaigrette
directions: Blend together in a bowl, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper. Slowly add oil while mixing with a
wire whisk.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut out stem ends of tomatoes and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Mix cornmeal, salt, sugar and pepper in a shallow dish.
Coat both sides of tomato.
Melt Crisco in a large skillet over medium heat. Add as many tomato slices at one time as will lie flat in skillet.
Lightly brown both sides, turning once; cook only until tender.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot overnight on low.
Drain and shred meat.
Add sauce and brown sugar to taste.
Cook for 4 hours on low.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg.
Add peaches.
Mix lightly and spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Combine melted butter, sugar, orange rind and nuts.
Sprinkle over peaches and continue baking for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: banana cheese pie(this pie is for banana lovers.)
directions: In pie shell, arrange sliced bananas.
In a bowl, mix well remaining ingredients, then pour over bananas.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Blend ingredients into dough.
Place in bowl and chill for 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Using tins with 1 dozen spaces, place one ball in each mold of tart tin.
With thumb, mold dough into shape of little shell.

title: glazed baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Stick ham with cloves. Bake, uncovered (no water added), for 50 minutes.
Baste with orange juice and brown sugar.
Keep putting on ham until browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and zucchini and dry ingredients. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before slicing.

title: real russian tea
directions: Bring 12 cups water to boil and pour over tea bags.
Bring to a boil (but don't boil) 3 cups water and cloves.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.

title: apple zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar.
Add rest of the ingredients until well blended.
Can be baked in large cake pan or in small bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and lemon extract.
Gradually stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Add egg yolks and stir until well blended. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites. Beat until almost stiff.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Put on pie filling.
Bake in slow oven at 325° until lightly browned.

title: white wine sangria punch
directions: Combine frozen lemonade and orange juice concentrate with water; mix well. Just before serving, mix in club soda and white wine. Garnish with orange slices and cherries. This mix freezes well, just take out of freezer a couple of hours before serving. (Can be served over crushed ice or ice cubes.)

title: sunday french toast
directions: Arrange bread in single layer in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. In a medium bowl, beat eggs with milk, orange juice, sugar, vanilla and salt until well blended.
Pour over bread, turning slices to coat evenly. Refrigerate, covered, overnight. Saute bread in hot skillet with butter until golden. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serves 4.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix in mayonnaise well.

title: milk delight punch
directions: Dissolve lime flavored gelatin in hot water. Cool slightly. Mix together all the ingredients except ginger ale and freeze in trays. Empty contents of trays in punch bowl and pour in chilled ginger ale. Will serve 50 in punch cups.

title: stir-fry
directions: Place oil in large skillet or wok.
Lightly stir-fry chicken. Remove meat.
Add onion, stir-fry vegetables, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry vegetables just until tender.
Add chicken to this mixture.
Do not overcook vegetables.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, bouillon, pepper and water.
Pour this mixture over chicken and vegetables in skillet.
Stir constantly and cook only a minute or two until thickened.
Serve over hot rice.

title: cajun hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonful in hot oil. Cook until well browned.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut and put in bottom of lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake as directed on box, then pour over coconut and pecan mixture.
Mix cream cheese, oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla and spread over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: curry chicken
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together. Place chicken breasts in baking dish sprayed with cooking spray. Pour soup mixture over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture, then cover with bread crumbs.
Dot margarine on top of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(May be prepared ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and let congeal.

title: easy no bake nut roll
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into 9 x 13 inch dish sprayed with Pam or butter. Add a little water if mixture is too dry to mix. Refrigerate for a few hours then cut into slices to eat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all cheese ingredients together.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in pecan pieces and top with cherry.
May use any flavor of cheese as long as 1 is a sharp cheese.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: In small bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Use as a substitute for 1 egg.
Yields 1 serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put tapioca over peaches; add sugar, if needed.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 6 tablespoons butter.
Beat the egg with the
milk; stir into flour mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls over peaches.
Bring to boil 3/4 cup sugar, 1/2 cup water and 3 tablespoons butter. Pour this over batter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix potatoes as directed on package in a 2-quart ovenproof dish.
Mix together ham, peas, onion, pepper and celery; add to casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until potatoes are tender.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion; saut until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Slit 6 double-thick pork chops from outer edge to bone to make a pocket. Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper inside and out.
Stuff loosely with dressing mixture.
Brown in skillet 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake in oven, covered, 45 minutes; uncover 15 minutes or until tender (350°).

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Cream butter until light.
Blend in sifted flour and baking powder.
Mix together.
Mix sweetener, vanilla and milk (or other liquid).
Mix well.
Sprinkle cinnamon over dough and knead until there are no streaks.
Shape dough into balls about 1/2-inch and arrange on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: apple syrup
directions: Blend
ingredients briefly on high.
Pour into saucepan and cook
over
medium
heat, stir constantly until thick and clear. Keep refrigerated.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix all of the above and enjoy.

title: peanut butter rocky road
directions: Lightly butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Over very low heat or in a double boiler, melt chips and peanut butter.
When melted, cool just a little.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cool.
Cut when cold.

title: custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt with an electric mixer.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until inserted table knife comes out clean.

title: cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients, adding beer last.
Makes a lot!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken (about 4 breasts) and pick off bone.
Cut cheese into chunks.
Prepare dressing following package directions, using chicken broth mixed with water for liquid.
Place frozen broccoli in pan and cover with some cheese.
Next, put the chicken on.
Put soup on and then a layer of cheese.
Last put the dressing on. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes covered and then 35 minutes uncovered.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 375° to 400° for about 25 or 30 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together and add celery seed dressing just before serving.

title: chocolate crispies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine butter, brown sugar, sugar and egg.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in chocolate flavoring.
Add flour and oats.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: peanut brittle ii
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients on medium high heat until the color changes to caramel.
Remove from heat and add soda; the candy will foam.
Quickly pour onto a butter sheet of foil.
Let cool then break into pieces.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Placed frozen roast in crock-pot.
Salt and pepper to taste and add onion.
Cook on high for 5 hours.

title: lazy day beef stew
directions: Brown beef with onion in oil in saucepan, stirring until beef is evenly browned on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours or longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: *Celery, cucumber, onion, green peppers (1 cup total, not each).

title: banana split delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of batter into small bowl; stir in cocoa.
Stir cherries in remaining batter; spread in pan.
Drop cocoa batter by tablespoons on top of batter in pan; cut through with knife for marbled effect.
Bake; cool completely.
Beat cream and sugar in chilled bowl until stiff; spread over cake.
Refrigerate.
Serve with fudge topping and cherries.
Makes 12 servings.

title: skillet barbecued chicken
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken on all sides in hot oil. Blend together remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Turn chicken and baste with sauce now and then.

title: sugar-free lucky if you have any left cake
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts until blended.
Smooth into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned; let cool.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown and chop beef and onion. Mix rest of ingredients in saucepan. Add browned meat and onion. Simmer for 1 to 2 hours on low-medium heat. Add pasta, if desired.

title: deviled ham
directions: In small bowl, thoroughly mix ham, mustard, cayenne and Worcestershire.
Melt butter in small saucepan and add mix.
Cook over medium heat until it begins to sizzle.
Serve on toast points.

title: aunt daisy's marmalade-raisin cookies
directions: Beat together marmalade, shortening and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and then the flavorings and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Grate
cheese
and
mix with Bisquick.	Crumble sausage and mix with other ingredients.
Make soft dough and roll out like biscuits.
Cut
with
a
small cutter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add vanilla and butter flavor. Add flour and salt.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruit delight pie
directions: Place pecans in bottom of pie shell.
Mix confectioners sugar with cream cheese and spread over pecans. Spoon on a layer of strawberries, a layer of pineapple and a layer of bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; melt butter and cream with sugar. Add egg, yeast mixture and flour.
Stir until mixed well.
Drop by spoonfuls in well buttered muffin pan.

title: lemon bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together the egg, milk, oil, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add egg mixture to this; stir until moistened. Pour into 2 greased 6 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans onto a wire rack; cool.
Wrap and store overnight.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to banana mixture until well blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and season to taste.
You can add chili powder, cumin or just salt and pepper. Mix together soups, beans, Ro-Tel tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Mix well and heat.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Flour first 4 ingredients with 1/2 cup flour.
Sift remaining flour and soda.
Mix sugar, salt and eggs, one at a time.
Add margarine. Alternate buttermilk with flour into mixture.
Combine all ingredients together and bake in a tube pan which has been greased and floured. Cook at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Heat 2 cups fresh orange juice and 1 box powdered sugar until dissolved. Spoon over cake while hot and let stand in pan overnight.

title: quick peach pie
directions: Place 1 cup peaches in container of an electric blender or food processor; process until smooth.
Pour pureed peaches into a saucepan; add corn syrup, water and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining peach slices and lemon juice.
Spoon mixture into crust; top with whipped cream.
Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in order listed; shake well before serving.
Good on any kind vegetable salad.

title: black bean soup
directions: Prepare Beans:
Rinse beans in cold water in 5-quart Dutch oven over high heat.
Heat beans and 8 cups water to boiling; cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans and return to
Dutch oven.
Add 8 cups water, ham hocks and next 9 ingredients; over high heat, heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 3 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: marinade for chicken or steak
directions: Marinate chicken or steak in the mixture.
Grill, broil or bake until done.

title: red pepper coulis
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add the sweet red pepper and garlic and saute for 15 minutes.
Stir in the vinegar and sugar.
Add the red pepper flakes, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally over medium heat for 15 minutes more.
Stir in the tomatoes and basil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot with grilled sirloin or flank steak.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: * I have used cornflakes, croutons or stuffing mix.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Butter dish.
Place layer of asparagus, mix soup and water and put layer over asparagus.
Repeat layers until gone.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: In a large pot, bring to a boil the raisins, sugar, water, butter and Spry.
Do not stir!!!
Remove from stove; set aside to cool.
After this is cool, then stir in the eggs and spices.
Now fold in about half the flour, then the baking soda.
Now just keep adding flour until you get the right texture for a cake dough. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until lightly touched with fingertip doesn't leave depression.
I like to use this as a base for my fruit cake, by adding fruits and nuts after dough is ready.

title: creamy turkey 'n broccoli
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions. Stir in 1/2 can onions and spread over bottom of 9 x 9-inch casserole dish. Arrange broccoli around outer edges of dish.
(You may use 1/2 head of fresh broccoli, slightly cooked.)
Mix undiluted soup with milk, sour cream and turkey in a bowl.
(You may use 1 cup milk for extra moistness.)
Spread this mixture over the broccoli and stuffing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining onions over turkey and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil in a 3-quart pan.
Remove from heat and add the peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
In a double boiler, melt the butterscotch and chocolate tidbits.
Pour over Rice Krispies mixture.
Smooth over top.
Chill, remove and cut into bars.

title: barbecued chicken or pork
directions: Fill slow cooker with meat. Cook on high for about 2 hours. Take meat out and discard liquid. Return meat to cooker. Pour barbecue sauce over meat. Cook another 2 hours. Spoon barbecue sauce and juice from bottom of cooker over meat. Lower heat to low and let set for an additional 2 hours. When done, meat will almost fall from bone. Have towels ready, can be very messy!

title: tuna stuffed jalapenos
directions: Slice peppers in half; seed and cut off stems.
Drain on paper towel for 1 hour, if possible.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place into a greased 2 qt. casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute bacon, onion and ground beef; drain juice.
Drain all beans except pork and beans.
Put all ingredients in a dish and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
You can really use any combination of beans.
This can be made ahead of time and baked when needed. Great for summer picnics.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Boil potatoes and mash well with butter.
Line a buttered pie dish with potatoes.
Boil onion 5 minutes and add rest of vegetables.
Cook until just tender.
Drain well.
Meanwhile, make a white sauce.
Melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in 1/4 cup flour and add 1 cup milk gradually and stir until boiling.
Place 1/2 vegetables in prepared pie dish.
Add salt and pepper, a layer of sauce, more vegetables, salt and pepper and sauce again.
Cover with remaining potatoes.
Smooth off sides and bake at 350° until brown.

title: deviled egg casserole
directions: Grind egg yolks and add ham, onions and parsley.
Mix in margarine, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Stuff eggs with mixture.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate morsels (microwave works fine).
Add the next 5 ingredients and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into pastry shell and top with remaining pecans.
Bake on bottom shelf of oven at 400° for 5 minutes; then lower temperature to 275° and bake 40 minutes.
Cool and serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: klop
directions: Mix ingredients and form into balls.
Brown in small amount of oil.

title: round steak roll-up
directions: In a bowl, break up bread and sprinkle with thyme, parsley, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Saute celery and onion in butter. Add to bread and mash together.
This is your stuffing.
(You may need to add some water to your stuffing.)

title: breakfast shake
directions: Mix or beat until smooth.
Serve in chilled glasses.
Add sprig of mint.

title: chuck roast
directions: Wash roast and lightly salt.
Place in crock-pot.
Do not add water.
Pour A.1. sauce and soup over roast and cook on slow until tender.
Thicken broth with cornstarch to make gravy.

title: baked steak supper
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place a piece of foil in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spray foil with Pam.
Pour Worcestershire over both sides of meat and sprinkle Creole seasoning over both sides of meat.
Place meat on foil in pan.
Spread soup over top of meat.
Place onions over soup.
Top with other vegetables.
Sprinkle water over vegetables.
Sprinkle vegetables lightly with Creole seasoning. Fold foil over and close securely.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve on platter.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Beat together.
Stir in 2 teaspoons minced green onion.
Can add finely chopped tomatoes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done and cut into cubes.
In a medium bowl, stir together soup and rotel.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with crushed chips.
Place chicken on top of chips and cover with shredded cheese.
Pour soup mixture over casserole.
Top with another layer of cheese and another layer of chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix together soup and sour cream.
Add chicken and stir.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle crackers evenly on top. Chip butter on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles. Then it is ready.
This recipe can be halved for a smaller casserole.

title: best chicken ever
directions: Place chicken breast in casserole dish. Sprinkle with black pepper. Pour Texas Pete Hot Sauce over chicken. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: quick hamburger stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours. Serve over biscuits.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You may not need a whole jar of salsa.
Add a small amount at a time to taste.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in buttered baking dish.
Add cinnamon and water.
Combine butter, sugar and flour.
Mix until it is crumbly. Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until juice seeps on top of apples and it is golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream, milk or ice cream.

title: mississippi mud cake(version 1)
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, cream margarine and sugar on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla, flour and cocoa. Blend well.
Fold in pecans and coconut on lowest speed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Spread Marshmallow Creme over warm cake.
Cool.

title: vanilla texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Bring 1/2 cup margarine, oil and water to a boil and pour over flour mixture; beat thoroughly. Beat in eggs, 2 teaspoons vanilla, cinnamon, soda and buttermilk. Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: charlie's brook trout supreme
directions: Sprinkle brook trout inside and out with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine the egg with the milk. Dip the trout in the mixture. Coat with bread crumbs.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large frying pan. Add fish and saute until golden brown on both sides, around 3 to 4 minutes.
Melt the remaining butter in another frying pan. Add the mushrooms, 1 tablespoon of the lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Saute mushrooms until hot.

title: the thing
directions: Brown ground beef in 8 inch skillet. Drain. Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes. Serve on buns.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Dice up onion and bell pepper and cook with margarine until tender. Stir in chicken soup and Ro-Tel. In a 9 x 13 pan, spray with Pam and layer tortillas, sauce and cheese. Layer several times. Cook for 35 minutes. Top with cheese. Bake for 5 minutes longer. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to thicken.

title: creamy potatoes
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Put in a large 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
On the top of the creamy potatoes add 2 cups of corn flakes.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dump all ingredients into a large bowl. Mash it!
Knead it!
Pound it!
The longer you mix it, the better it tastes.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together the sugar, oil and eggs.
Mash bananas.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture; beat well.
Add mashed bananas and nuts until well blended.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Bread is done when it doesn't stick by testing with a toothpick.

title: taco soup
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef, onion and taco seasoning. In a 2-quart stewpan, mix together tomatoes, corn, beans and water.
Stir in ground beef mixture.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: creamy potato sticks
directions: In saucepan, combine flour and salt. Gradually whisk in milk until smooth. Bring to boil. Cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Whisk in soup and cheese until smooth. Set aside. Cut potatoes into 4 x 1/2-inch sticks. Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with onion. Top with cheese sauce. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes until tender. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: best ever coleslaw
directions: Use blender.
Fill with cut up vegetables and cover with water to blend.
Drain.
Dump all shredded vegetables in a large bowl. Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, celery seed, salt and dry mustard in saucepan.
Bring to boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Stir in, cover and cool.

title: hash browns
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in cake pan. Spray cake pan with Pam.

title: cheeseburger biscuit pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease 9-inch pie pan. Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Press 6 biscuits over bottom and up the sides of the pie pan to form crust. Cut the other 4 biscuits into quarters and set aside. Brown ground beef and onion until thoroughly cooked; drain. Add ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper. Heat until bubbly. Spoon into biscuit-lined pan. Arrange cheese slices on top of beef mixture. Place biscuit quarters, point side down, around the edge of the pie pan. Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: deviled steak
directions: Trim fat from steak and slice in thin, 2-inch strips. Coat with flour and brown with onion and garlic in the oil. Stir in water, tomato sauce, vinegar, horseradish, mustard and seasonings. Cover and simmer until tender, stirring occasionally, scraping bottom of pan. Add water as needed. Serve over noodles or with mashed potatoes. Makes 5-6 servings.

title: healthy apple sandwiches
directions: Saturate apples in lemon juice.
Remove from juice.
Add peanut butter and bacon.
Spread on bread.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all.
Cut out center of Vienna loaf of bread.
Cut center into bite-size pieces.
Place dip in center of bread.
Place center pieces around loaf.

title: snickerdoodles or sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pauline's baked lima beans
directions: Drain canned lima beans and save liquid.
Cut bacon into small pieces.
Stir all ingredients together.
Add more bean liquid if needed.
Lay several more bacon strips across top of beans.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Boil roast in water that covers
it
(to which has been added cloves and sliced onion)
until pork is cooked thoroughly.	Let cool in liquid and then
remove
all fat; chop up the pork.
(This can be done ahead
and
stored
in the refrigerator.) Put pork in crock-pot
with
barbecue
sauce and chopped onion.
Cover and cook in crock-pot 2
to 3 hours (until onion is done) on high or on low for	4
hours
or
more.
Serve
in large buns with coleslaw or pickles.

title: beef and squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in salted water 5 minutes and drain well.
Cook green peppers and meat until meat is no longer pink. Stir in rice.
Blend eggs, soup, sour cream and seasonings.
Stir into meat mixture.
Fold in squash.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Put in apples and cook.
Mix brown sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over apples.
May need about 1/4 cup of water added.
When apples are beginning to get done, pour into a deep dish pie shell.
Top with 1/2 stick of butter, 2/3 cup flour and 2/3 cup sugar.
Mix sugar and flour, then work in butter to make crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie and bake for a short while until topping is brown.
You may add pecans in topping.

title: canned zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until
light	and add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini; mix
well.
Add
sifted
dry ingredients;
mix well. Spray each jar
with
Pam.	Fill
jars just a little past half full with batter.
Bake
at
for 1 hour.
Have lids hot. Take jars out one
at
a time.
Wipe the top real well and put caps on.
Go to
next
jar.
Do
not
worry if they are higher than jar, just
push
down with lid.
These will seal and last up to 5 years.
They are moist and no freezer burn taste.
You can do this with any kind of bread or cake.

title: pedro's special
directions: Brown in little oil, meat, onion and garlic.
Stir in tomato sauce, oregano and chili powder.
Grease a good sized casserole and alternate layers of meat, beans and corn chips, ending with corn chips.
Bake it covered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover it and bake 10 minutes more.
Put shredded lettuce and finely chopped onion on top before serving.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together with 3 beaten eggs.
Add large can crushed pineapple (drained well) to mixture.
Remove crust from bread; break into pieces and add to mixture.
Add evaporated milk.
Mix well and put in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until top is brown.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except fruit.
Mix well, then add fruit.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream together 2/3 cup margarine, sugar and salt until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, then 1 teaspoon vanilla. Blend in flour, one cup at a time.
Cover and chill 1 hour. Preheat oven to 375°.
Divide dough in half.
On lightly floured board, roll out each half to 1/8-inch thickness.
With a 2 1/4-inch fluted-edge cookie cutter, cut dough into rounds.
With a 1/2-inch round cutter, cut out centers from half of rounds.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown. Cool on racks.

title: triple chocolate rocky road bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix cookie mix (dry), oil, water and egg with spoon until dough forms. Press in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2 inches.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or just until set. Cool completely.
Mix frosting and marshmallows; spread over bars. Sprinkle with peanuts. Cut into about 2 inch squares.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Brown beef and onion in a large skillet.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, garlic salt and oregano; boil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer 1/3 noodles, 1/3 sauce and 1/3 cottage, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses in a 2-quart buttered rectangular baking dish.
Repeat twice.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
How about doing two and freeze one. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hearty tomato-bean soup
directions: Saute chopped onions in margarine until soft.
Add hot dog pennies and saute for 2 minutes.
Add soups and water and blend gently to get lumps out.
Add seasonings.
Enjoy!

title: iced tea syrup
directions: In a large saucepan, mix sugar and water and bring to a boil. Boil 3 minutes and remove from heat. Add tea bags or loose tea. Cover with a tight-fitting lid and let tea steep overnight or until syrup is cold. Pour through a fine strainer and store in refrigerator. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Cook beef and onion in skillet until brown. Drain. Stir in soup, vegetables and milk.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1 pint strawberries.
Cook slowly with cornstarch and sugar until thick and clear.
Bake pie crust.
Slice 1 pint strawberries into crust; top with cooked mixture.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Mix sugar, eggs, oil and flavoring; mix well. Sift flour and soda together and mix. Add apples and pecans. Bake in a pan for 30 minutes, or until cake comes from side of the pan.

title: bannocks(breakfast quick bread)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a baking sheet.
Put oats, flour and salt into a mixing bowl and stir with a fork to blend.
Cut in margarine and cinnamon.
Rub mix together until coarse bits form. Stir in the water and mix.
Gather the dough and place on lightly floured board.
Knead about 6 times.
Divide the dough in half and pat each half into a circle about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut each circle into pie shaped wedges.
Place wedges on greased cookie sheet 1/2-inch apart.
Bake about 20 minutes or until lightly colored.

title: microwave spicy pecans
directions: In a glass pie plate, melt butter for 30 seconds on High.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Toss pecans into mixture to coat. Microwave for 4 to 6 minutes on High, stirring twice.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and cayenne pepper.

title: lemonade ice cream pie
directions: Place pie crusts in freezer.
Put softened ice cream, lemonade concentrate and 3/4 of the whipped topping into a large bowl.
Stir until blended.
(I used my mixer to blend it together.)
Spread 1/2 of mixture in each pie crust.
Top each with remaining whipped topping.
Freeze just until topping is firm, then cover airtight with foil or plastic wrap.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Serve garnished with lemon slices and mint.

title: pink divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in buttered, heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Then cook, without stirring, to hard-ball stage, 250°.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites in large bowl of mixer until soft peaks form.
Gradually add gelatin, beating until stiff peaks form.
Slowly pour in syrup, beating constantly at high speed.
Continue beating until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Stir in chopped nuts
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper or into small paper muffin liners.
Makes about 4 dozen medium-sized pieces of candy.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and garlic in frying pan until done.
When brown, add a glass of water.
Brown celery, pepper, garlic and onions in frying pan with butter and some oil to keep from burning.
Add meat; using large pot, add the season in the mixture, also 1/4 pound cheese.
If dry, add more tomato sauce and water, if needed. Cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours.

title: sloop
directions: Brown and drain chopped meat.
Combine carrots, celery, onion and garlic.
Add packages for brown gravy.
Simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
The last 15 to 20 minutes, add sour cream.
Stir to creamy mixture.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: cookie salad
directions: In a bowl, break up cookies into quarter size.
Reserve a few whole ones for decorations on top of salad.
Add all remaining ingredients. Blend with spatula.
Place whole cookies on top. Chill until ready to serve.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Thaw broccoli and squeeze dry.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine vegetable soup mix, sour cream, broccoli and 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese until smooth.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and toasted bread in greased cooking pan. Add stuffing mix; set aside.
In saucepan, cook onion and celery in water until veggies are done.
Beat eggs; add cool turkey drippings, poultry seasoning, sage and salt to taste.
Add to bread mixture and toss.
If not moist, add more drippings. Consistency should be similar to stiff cornbread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: salsa chops
directions: Spray skillet with no stick cooking spray.
Brown chops over medium-high heat on both sides.
Turn heat to medium-low and add salsa.
Cook on medium-low for 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Combine egg, oil and strawberries; add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Freezes well.

title: elsie's marmalade drop cookies
directions: Mix together the marmalade, shortening, egg, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix in the flour a little at a time and the raisins and walnuts last.
Drop from a tablespoon on a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350-375° oven until tester is clean when withdrawn from a cookie.

title: bridget's best soup
directions: Cover ham with water.
Bring to a boil, turn down, simmer for 1 hour.
Remove meat.
Add beans and potatoes.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces and return to broth.
When beans and potatoes are cooked, soup is done, about 1 hour.

title: red drop salad
directions: Use 1 cup boiling water to dissolve cinnamon drops.
Dissolve remaining water and Jell-O and add well dissolved drops.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
When about half set, stir well and refrigerate.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: This recipe requires an apple which will keep its shape (Yellow Delicious are especially good.)

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish. Melt the butter in a skillet and cook the onion over medium heat until soft.
In a small bowl, mix the eggs and sour cream, then add the onion, cheese and ham.
Add salt to taste.
Put the noodles in the casserole.
Then add the sauce and toss gently. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: almond cranberry punch
directions: Put first five ingredients in punch bowl.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add ginger ale.
Add ice block or mold.

title: taffies(cookies)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate and flour.
Add flour slowly.
When dough is pliable, press out on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When done, and while very hot, lay the chocolate bars on top, or sprinkle with the chocolate chips.
Spread chocolate across dough as it melts.
Let cool before cutting into serving pieces.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and shortening. Blend well. Sift dry ingredients together. Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Blend well. Pour into greased shallow cake pan.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes. Cut into bars. Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 24.

title: meat pasties
directions: Fry meat, potatoes, onion and garlic together until done. Drain off fat.
Stir in cinnamon, salt, pepper and carrots.

title: mrs. mckenney's fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and fruit cocktail.
Add all can fruit in bowl. Sprinkle vanilla pudding on top.
Stir.
Add Cool Whip.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and chopped walnuts on top.

title: easy tamale pie
directions: Place mashed tamales in a deep dish.
Top with chili and minced onion.
Mix corn chips and cheese; sprinkle over all. Sprinkle with chopped tomato and onion.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies in food processor until they resemble dirt. Layer 1/2 of the cookies in pan of flowerpot.
Blend cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar until light.
Add vanilla and fold in Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and milk. Bring to a full boil. Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 glass dish. Cool.

title: no fuss meat loaf
directions: Place meat, stuffing mix, salt and pepper in a large bowl, combine stewed tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce in blender or food processor.
Whirl until tomatoes are crushed.
Add to meat mixture and mix lightly.
Press into loaf pan and brush with catsup before baking, if desired.
Bake for 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: sun-drop pound cake
directions: Mix as listed.
Alternate flour and Sun-Drop until well mixed. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pineapple and frosting.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
After you take the cake out of oven, pour pineapple and juice all over cake, then let it cool about 10 minutes.
Spread vanilla frosting over top. Serve from pan.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and chop.
Saute vegetables with parsley and add seasonings, then add soups and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Boil noodles in chicken broth.
Drain and pour noodles into Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Add chicken/soup mixture to noodles and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Mix together cocoa or chocolate and melted butter.
Add eggs and stir.
Add sugar and salt and mix.
Fold in flour; add vanilla.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon for each cookie in waffle iron. Bake for 60 seconds and remove from waffle iron with a fork. Frost with frosting.

title: sausage bake
directions: Beat eggs, half and half, salt and mustard together.
Put cubed bread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage over top, pour eggs over and add cheese to top.
Let sit overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: sugarless apple pie(good for diabetic)
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix together the apple juice, sweeteners, margarine and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Pour over apples and mix well.
Pour apples into 1 Pet Ritz pie shell and top with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: creamy chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put ingredients in pan in order they come.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dutch cocoa hot fudge sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until butter is melted.
Reduce heat and continue to stir until sugar is dissolved (about 5 minutes).
Serve immediately.

title: cranberry sauce jello mold
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add in the dissolved Knox gelatine.
Add the raspberry sherbet and lemon juice.
Chop the cranberry sauce into pea size pieces and add to the mix.
Pour into a circle mold and refrigerate for 2 days.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease sheet cake pan.
Spread coconut over the crushed pineapple.
Spread cherry pie filling over coconut.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling.
Top with nuts and pats of butter.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sliced apples in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan or baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread the mixture over the apples.
Bake in oven 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and the topping is golden brown.

title: barbecued pork chinese style
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork.
Rub into pork loin and marinate 3 to 4 hours.
Roast in a 350° oven on rack for 25 minutes.
Turn over and bake 25 minutes more.
Serve with Chinese style hot mustard and sesame seed.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Put dates in bowl; sprinkle with soda, then add hot water. Set aside.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Put on crust in bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Toss with berries.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Brush lightly with milk. Slit crust with knife.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Serve while warm.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Pour into greased Pyrex deep dish, 10-inch preferably.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown around edges.

title: new york cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage. Add sugar, vinegar and olive oil; toss. Taste and adjust if desired. Add next 3 ingredients. Mix well and chill.

title: chocolate chip banana cake
directions: *Can use 1/2 whole wheat flour and 1/2 enriched, but not all whole wheat, too heavy.

title: christmas rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Pour into two round cake pans.
Bake as directed.
Cool cake 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pans.
Cool completely.
Place cake layer with top side up back into two clean pans.
Poke holes in each layer with a fork.
Pour one cup boiling water in raspberry Jell-O.
Pour 1 cup boiling water in lime Jell-O.
Put raspberry Jell-O slowly over 1 layer, lime Jell-O over other layer.
Might be best to spoon Jell-O on cake layers. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Dip in warm water to get cake out. Frost one layer; put other on top.
Frost.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: pfeffernuesse
directions: Mix ingredients; cool at least 2 hours.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip in powdered sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: hunters stew
directions: Dice sausage; boil sausage while paring potatoes (about 1/2 hour).
Dice potatoes; cook with sausage until potatoes are done (about 15 minutes).
Add corn and beans; heat to boiling.
Serve.

title: 3 bean baked beans
directions: Browned, drained and chopped bacon or browned and drained ground beef can also be added, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or can be baked in crock-pot.

title: layered dip
directions: Layer these ingredients in a dish and serve with chips. Serves 15.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Cream the butter and add the sugar, creaming while adding. Add eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add the vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken and spaghetti(italian)
directions: Cook chicken and garlic in olive oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat until chicken is browned, turning once.
Add tomato paste and next 7 ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve over pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 6 servings.

title: best cake
directions: Mix by hand flour, eggs, sugar, vanilla, soda, walnuts and undrained pineapple.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, 4 beaten eggs, cooking oil and 7-Up. Bake in a greased and slightly-floured (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into baking dish and spread with the Topping.

title: fiesta fish
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
marinate fish fillets for 20 minutes or longer.	Bake or broil as usual.

title: applesauce-raisin cookies
directions: Cream the oil and sugar together.
Add the egg; beat until light.
Blend in the vanilla and applesauce.
Stir the two flours, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, oatmeal and raisins into the creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly oiled baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil in blender.
Turn on low; slowly add oil.
Blend 5 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: frosting
directions: Mix all together. Beat until mixture is creamy.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon onto slightly greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: dilled green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes in wedges.
Combine the vinegar, water and salt; bring to a boil (keep hot but not boiling).
Pack tomatoes into warm jars with garlic, dill and bay leaf.
Add liquid to 1/4 inch below tops of jars.
Clean rims and put on lids with caps; do not seal tightly.
Process for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from boiling bath and let cool.

title: dillie bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in saucepan the cottage cheese, sugar, onion and butter.
Place in mixer, dill seed, soda, eggs and softened yeast.
Add flour to form stiff dough.
First addition of flour, use mixer on low speed.
Add cottage cheese mixture to mixer; beat well until batter cleans sides of bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down dough.
Form and turn in 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Poke holes with fork in dough.
This makes a very stiff dough when baked.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn out on towel. Butter and sprinkle top with kosher salt.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice in 10-inch dish. Add salt and water. Lay pork chops over rice and sprinkle with dry soup mix. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green bean salad
directions: Cook bacon until well done and crisp.
Crumble.
Add drippings and chopped onions to rest of ingredients.
This may be served hot or cold.

title: mom's red devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients with 1 cup buttermilk alternately.
Stir in vanilla. Pour in boiling water all at once and stir until combined.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes or sheet cake for 45 minutes. Top with favorite frosting.

title: white bread
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Pour into large bowl; add sugar, butter and salt.
Stir well until sugar is dissolved.
Set aside to cool to 130°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: rice soup
directions: Combine broth and tomato sauce in a large pan.
Bring to a slow boil. Add rice. Cook until rice is done, then add cheese.

title: fluffy lime jello(serves 20)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Put in blender with cream cheese.
Drain pears and blend.
Chill until thickened.
Mix Dream Whip and fold in.
Refrigerate.

title: forty-niners
directions: Beat eggs well, add sugar and Bisquick; mix well.
Add pecans and pour into a 9 x 13-inch well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients; mix well.
Add milk; stir. Pour mixture into a lightly greased, shallow 2-quart casserole. Dot with butter.
Spoon peaches over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until browned.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Heat Karo syrup and sugar; add peanut butter.
Cook and stir until this gets real hot.
Do not boil.
Take off heat and mix Rice Krispies.
Coat real good.
By the time you get it all coated you will be able to roll out in small balls.

title: sopaipilla burgers
directions: In large bowl, cut 2 tablespoons shortening into flour until mixture resembles corn meal.
Gradually stir in water until crumbly dough forms.
Press dough together with hands.
Knead about 5 minutes on lightly floured surface.
Cover; let rest 5 minutes.
Prepare Ground Beef Filling; keep warm.
Cut dough in 12 equal pieces; shape each into a ball.
Flatten and roll each into 9-inch circles.
In deep fat fryer, heat remaining 5 cups shortening to 370°.
Cook one at a time, turning once, until golden.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar; add eggs and beat well. Stir dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with applesauce. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Put in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.
Serve with Cool Whip or lemon sauce.

title: yam casserole
directions: Heat canned yams in syrup for about 5 minutes, then drain. Place in mixing bowl.
Add butter and milk; mash.
Add raisins; mix.
Place in greased baking dish; top with marshmallows.
Bake in oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until brown.
Serves 7.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Stir in eggs and molasses.
Add vinegar and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in and mix well.
Chill overnight.
Place 1 small ball on cookie sheet, flatten with palm to make head.
Roll another ball into a straight rope for arms.
Roll another ball into a rope and then curve it for legs and body. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Garnish with nuts or raisins before baking.
Continue with this shaping process until greased cookie sheet is full, but leave adequate space for cookie to spread.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together and stir.
Put in a casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Mix 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs and press into a square pan.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello, sugar and boiling water until jello dissolves.
Add juices and cold water.
Freeze for 24 hours.

title: crunchy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl beat butter, sugars, egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture (slowly) alternating with oil.
Stir in cereal and chips.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Make crust.
Mix pudding mix according to directions on box. After crust is cooled, place a thin coat of pudding on bottom. Slice in banana.
Keep layering.
Spread Cool Whip
(which is at room temperature) on top.
Garnish with walnuts.

title: chicken, rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and top.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets.
Leave 2 inches of stem and tap root.
Cover with boiling water.
Cook until done.
Peel and cut off tap root. Combine all ingredients except beets.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pack beets into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch at top of jar.
Cut large beets into smaller pieces.
Remove cinnamon.
Bring liquid to boil.
Pour boiling hot over beets, leaving 1/2-inch space. Process jars 30 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: chicken-dressing bake
directions: Toss stuffing mix with half can of the soup, the chicken broth and beaten eggs.
Spread mixture in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Top with the cooked chicken or turkey.
Combine remaining half can of soup with milk and pimiento; pour over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marie's ohio brownies
directions: Boil 1 minute.
Let cool 10 minutes and beat until spreading consistency.
Spread on baked brownies.

title: hungarian receipt stuffed peppers paprika
directions: Cut tops off each pepper; remove seeds.
Cook peppers in boiling salt water to cover for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine pork, onion and garlic in a skillet.
Cook until pork is browned.
Drain and cool.
Add salt, paprika, pepper, rice and egg to pork mixture; mix well.
Combine tomato paste and water.
Add 1 cup to pork mixture.
Stuff peppers with pork mixture and place in a shallow pan.
Put remaining tomato mixture over peppers.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: banana oat muffins
directions: In a large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and sugar about 1 minute until blended and sugar is free of lumps.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1 tablespoon oats; beat about 1 minute just until batter is smooth.
Spoon batter into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups; sprinkle with reserved oats.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar and milk; bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes. While still boiling, add the peanut butter and margarine.
Stir and cool in cold water until it starts to thicken.
Drop rapidly onto wax paper.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler or in microwave; add sweetened condensed milk and nuts.
Stir to mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish (or use smaller for thicker fudge). Let cool.
Will take several hours for fudge to set.
Cut into squares.

title: beef stroganoff rice salad
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in rice and salt.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand covered until all water is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to bowl.
Cover and chill.
Add mushrooms, celery and green onions to rice.
Mix well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Place Veg-All, kidney beans, whole corn, celery, green pepper and onion in bowl.
Combine flour, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
In a saucepan, cook until the mixture thickens.
Set aside to cool. When cool, pour it over vegetables and mix.

title: harvest cubed beets
directions: Boil 5 minutes. Let stand 30 minutes. Warm up. Add 3 tablespoons butter, then eat.

title: purple cow milk shake
directions: Place the yogurt, milk, grape juice concentrate and lemon juice in a blender container. Blend until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: mac's ham special
directions: Trim all fat and skin off shoulder that you can.
Place in a slow cooker with half bottle of vinegar and 1/8 bottle of hot sauce.
Let cook on low overnight, or about 8 hours.
Drain all juice and put other half bottle of vinegar and 1/8 bottle of hot sauce.
Cook about 4 hours or until you are ready to eat.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Shred and cook cabbage for 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
Saute in butter the garlic, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour soup mixture over cabbage.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole pan that has been layered with cooked rice. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat in oil.
Arrange potatoes, carrots and celery around meat and season with salt and pepper.
Place apricots on top of meat and pour ketchup over all.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, basting occasionally.
Other vegetables may be added.

title: holiday cream pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until light and smooth.
Whip the cream.
Blend one half into cheese mixture. Fold second half of whipped cream into mixture.
Place into pie shell.
Chill for several hours.
Top with fresh or frozen fruit such as strawberries, raspberries or peaches.

title: honolulu salad
directions: Beat Dream Whip by directions on box.
Set aside.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Mix all together and decorate with a few pieces of cherries and pecans.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Blend in flour.
Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in vegetables and seasonings and egg.
Heat.
Spoon chicken mixture into a 1 1/2-quart dish and top with the biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
It takes about 14 biscuits, cut into quarters.

title: quick spinach lasagna
directions: Mix and heat in saucepan the Prego, tomato paste and water. In large mixing bowl, combine together the frozen spinach, 2 eggs, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
In large baking pan, layer sauce, raw noodles, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese until you reach the top of the pan.
End up with sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: *Option:
Use 1 cup crunchy peanut butter instead of chopped nuts and regular peanut butter.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Trim excess fat from approximately 7 pounds of beef or pork ribs; sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Add Crisco or oil to large pot and brown ribs.
Add enough water to cover meat and onion, vinegar, salt and whole peppercorns.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Drain water and place ribs on hot outdoor grill.
Baste with barbecue sauce and cook until desired crispiness.

title: cheese-cucumber souffle salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water, vinegar, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Chill until almost firm.
Add cottage cheese, cucumber and onion.
Pour into mold.

title: herbed new york strip steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Combine thyme and the next
5 herbs and seasonings.
Mix well, mashing with back of spoon to bring out the flavor of the herbs.
Pat mixture on both sides of the steak.
Let set 10 minutes in refrigerator.
Heat olive oil in iron skillet.
Add chilled steak.
Cook 3 minutes on each side. Cover skillet with aluminum foil and bake in 450° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, according to your desired degree of doneness.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing into thin slices.
Yield: 6 servings.
Great for sandwiches also.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and baking soda.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and almond extract.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
