Bake in preheated 350° oven 10 minutes or until light golden brown. Let cookies cool 1 minute before removing them from cookie sheets to wire racks.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Split cake layers, if desired. Mix sugar, sour cream and strawberries. Use half for filling between layers. Mix remaining half with Cool Whip and use for frosting. Should be refrigerated for 2 days.

title: "doc's"  cornbread
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients.
Pour into a hot greased 7-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 25-30 minutes at 400.
Serves 4.

title: mrs. truman's ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg, add sugar and mix until smooth and creamy.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to egg mixture and blend.
Lastly, add the nutmeats, apple and vanilla and mix well. Pour into a large 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve warm with plain or whipped cream.

title: nutty fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa together.
Beat together with remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: spinach cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth. Mix in remainder of ingredients and pour into pie plate. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until cheese has melted. Bake in oven on broil for 5 to 10 minutes or until brown around the edges.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Then add shortening, egg, mashed bananas, rolled oats and chopped nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise and sugar.
Toss in with broccoli and put bacon bits or crumbled bacon on top.
(Can also add diced red onion to mixture, if desired.)
Can make a day ahead.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a medium saucepan heat cheese and cream, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted and sauce is creamy. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut shortening into the dry ingredients. Combine milk, eggs and vanilla, slightly beaten.
Add this to the dry ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Put all ingredients, except butter, in plastic bag, then put potatoes in and toss until well coated.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining flour mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350°, turning once while baking. Bake until tender.

title: pumpkin spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl combine flour, soda, salt and pumpkin pie spice.

title: nachos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning, water and taco sauce; let simmer.
Put tortilla chips on platter and melt Cheez Whiz.
Pour hamburger mixture over chips and then pour Cheez Whiz over mixture.
Add lettuce and chopped tomato on top. Serves 4.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Set aside 1/3.
Mix 2/3 Oreos with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Melt remaining butter and chocolate.
Add vanilla, 2 cups powdered sugar and 2 eggs and mix.
Spread over Oreos in pan.
(I refrigerate for a short time to let the fudge sauce firm up.) Soften ice cream and spread it on top.
Sprinkle rest of crushed Oreos.
Freeze.

title: chewy monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a tube pan.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix 3/4 cup of sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Drop biscuits into mixture and then drop evenly into cake pan.

title: scotch crispies
directions: Melt the chips and peanut butter over hot, not boiling, water. Stir until smooth; put in large bowl.
Add the corn
flakes; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Chill.

title: berry fluff
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat on Number 8 speed for 10 minutes, until mixture is very thick and fluffy. Nice to serve on angel food or any plain cake.

title: mom's six layer dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a greased casserole or slow cooker.
If baking, cover with lid and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Slow cooker should take about the same time.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: pasta primavera(light)
directions: In a pot, prepare spaghetti according to directions on package; drain.
Return spaghetti to pot to keep warm.
Meanwhile, in a 2-quart saucepan over high heat, in 1-inch boiling water, heat broccoli pieces to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is tender-crisp; drain.

title: pork sausage ring
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into a ring in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake 1 hour in 350° preheated oven.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with sugar.
Pour over broken pretzels in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper; drain grease. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture, then stir in chopped apples and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: appleade
directions: Dice apples and pour boiling water over them.
Add sugar and strain into a container.
Allow to cool.
Serve over ice with sliced apple to decorate.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Keep cool until ready to use.
Mixture will thicken after it's chilled.
Yields 14 ounces or 1 can Eagle Brand.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: Combine 1/3 cup sugar and cornstarch in heavy saucepan; stir until
blended.
Slowly
stir
in milk; bring to a boil. Cook
1 minute
or	until thickened; stir constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.

title: cheese filled manicotti
directions: Beat eggs with butter. Add remaining ingredients (except Ragu).
Mix well. Stuff uncooked noodles with cheese mixture. Mix Ragu and water.
Pour over manicotti.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: cracked wheat bulgar pilaf
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add egg noodles and stir until golden brown.
Add bulgar and stir.
Add chicken broth and chi chi peas.
Stir and cover.
Salt to taste. Reduce heat to low and cook until all liquid is absorbed.
Fluff with fork and serve.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add sauerkraut.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Pour Thousand Island on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: that green thing
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1 cup hot water; add 1 cup liquid from fruit cocktail (if not enough liquid, add enough water to make a cup).
Put gelatine, mayonnaise and cream cheese in food processor or blender and process.
Remove to mixing bowl and stir in fruit cocktail and pecans.
Pour into an oiled gelatin mold.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and spices together in bowl.
Stir in oats.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.
Fill greased muffin tins.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 15 minutes or until done.
Serve piping hot with apple butter or drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple and apples in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix over mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over mixture and then pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes.

title: deer jerky
directions: Use venison sliced in 1/8-inch strips.
The meat is combined with the ingredients listed, then it is sealed in a large plastic bag or large pan and placed in a refrigerator overnight to marinate.
I made it in my food dehydrator or you can make it in your microwave oven.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Flour chicken and brown in skillet.
Place in casserole.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Mix together oil, cocoa, margarine and sugar.
Blend 1 egg a a time.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Sift and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill to set dough.
Shape in 2-inch balls. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: kabob marinade
directions: Blend and top vegetables.
Best to let sit at least 2 hours; overnight is fine. Recommended veggies are:

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat 4 eggs in mixer.
Add sugar, cottage cheese and cream cheese; beat on high speed.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, flour, cornstarch, butter and sour cream.
Beat on medium speed until well blended.
Pour into buttered spring-form pan (no flour). Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until edge browns slightly.
Shut oven off and leave in oven 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs in a casserole dish.
Add cinnamon, sugar and milk. Mix well.
Tear bread slices into small pieces and mix into egg mixture.
Use enough bread so that egg mixture is not runny.
Dot with butter and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Do not use salt or pepper.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs and oil in small bowl.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add egg mixture; mix softly.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Do not overmix. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: fried bread
directions: Mix ingredients and form silver dollar size patties.
Fry in a pan of oil.
If the batter is too soupy, you may pour a cup at a time in hot oil.
Cover and turn when golden brown on one side.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats.
Cover let stand 20 minutes.
Beat butter until soft and creamy.
Add sugars. Blend in vanilla and eggs, stir in oats.
Sift flour, soda, salt, and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend and pour into greased and floured 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes.

title: superb salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Can be made one day ahead.

title: sock-it-to-me cake(coffee cake)
directions: Grease Bundt pan with 1/2 stick margarine.
Beat eggs.
Add cake mix, pudding, corn oil, water and flavorings.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl combine sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Layer 1/3 batter, 1/2 dry ingredients, 1/3 batter, 1/2 dry ingredients and 1/3 batter.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken and broccoli for "working parents"
directions: Brown chicken (cut in pieces).
Lower pan to cool down. (Steam or microwave box of broccoli.)
Add cream of mushroom soup and broccoli.
Stir.
Add cheese and Tabasco to taste.
(Add fresh sliced mushrooms, if desired; adds taste.)
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Total time: 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick milk chocolate fudge
directions: Note:
Be sure and use milk chocolate chips, not semi-sweet morsels.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large Dutch oven, melt stick of butter and saute onion until clear.
Add bell pepper and mushrooms and cook until soft. Add pimentos and Worcestershire sauce.
Reduce heat and add Velveeta cheese cubes.
Stir constantly until melted.
Add chicken and spaghetti.
Can be served immediately or transferred to a large baking dish and refrigerated.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.
Serve with garlic bread and green salad.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Roll and shape into 12 balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Put Hershey Kisses in center of balls and press down.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gretchen's coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine 2/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour and salt. Gradually add milk, mixing well.
Cook and stir over medium heat with wire whisk until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks; immediately return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup coconut.
Let stand while preparing meringue.

title: june's meat loaf
directions: Mix first seven ingredients and shape into a loaf pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting with the sauce mixture several times during baking.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Soak raisins in hot water about 30 minutes.
Drain.
In pan, cook until thick, all ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with beaten egg whites and brown.

title: easy chocolate layered dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients as for pie crust.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: hamburger and vegetable casserole
directions: In large casserole dish layer potatoes, onions, carrots, peas and corn.
Layer ground beef on top layer.
Cover with catsup. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Cook covered.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat. Boil 5 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla. Pour over popped corn.
If desired, add peanuts to syrup.
Pour syrup over corn. Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on waxed paper.
When cool, break apart.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour both cans of pineapple with the juice into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour both cans of cherry pie filling over the pineapple (do not mix).
Pour dry cake mix over and spread (do not mix).
Cut butter into 1/8-inch pats on top of cake mix.
Top with walnuts.
Bake 1 1/3 to 2 hours.

title: salmon romanoff
directions: Flake salmon and combine all ingredients.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add the dry ingredients.
Mix.
Add vanilla, coconut, dates, apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or use 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done (usually a little over 1 hour if pans ar small).
Serves 20 people.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
May be served slightly warm or served cooled.
Top with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: In food processor, chop up water chestnuts; add green onions and chop, then Knorr vegetable soup mix.
Stir in mayonnaise and sour cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with 2 cups Ritz cracker crumbs and 1 additional stick of melted margarine.
Cook 15 minutes more after spreading margarine over cracker crumbs.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Fry sausage until crumbly and then drain it.
Combine all ingredients and put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10. Ham or bacon can be used instead of sausage.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out bread and top with a thin layer of meat and cheese. Top with cooked peppers and onions, which have been cooked in melted butter.
Fold sides over, then ends under.
Place on a cookie sheet with folded side down.
Baste top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all together. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: quick fix mixed bean salad
directions: Empty contents of all cans into a large mixing bowl.
Cut onion into small pieces. Cover all ingredients with sweet and sour dressing.
Let stand refrigerated at least 2 hours.
"Enjoy".

title: tomato pie
directions: Line 11 x 13 Pyrex dish with biscuits. Layer tomatoes. Saut onion and pepper in butter. Spread on top. Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together. Spoon on top. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into an 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, egg, baking powder and enough water to form a stiff dough.
Divide dough into 3 parts and roll, one at a time, very thin on floured surface.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch strips and drop into broth.
Add chicken.
Serve hot.

title: pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese in pizza pan.
Combine ketchup, horseradish and shrimp.
Spread over the cream cheese.
Mix peppers, tomatoes, onions and olives and spread on next.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Place Wheat Thins around edge of "pizza."

title: crispy crab cakes
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender. Combine all remaining ingredients except vegetable oil, stirring well.
Form into patties 3 inches in diameter and 1/2-inch thick. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: fettuccine alla carbonara
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Meanwhile in a medium bowl, beat together eggs and cream just until blended.
Stir in cheese; set aside.
In a large kettle or Dutch oven, cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and immediately return to hot kettle.
Toss pasta with margarine or butter until melted.
Add bacon and cheese mixture. Toss gently until well mixed.
Transfer to a warm serving plate.

title: dad's chicken gravy
directions: Dip the chicken in flour.
Place skin side down in melted butter in a glass baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 20 minutes longer.
Pour off fat.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Mix in a bowl the milk, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture over the chicken and vegetables. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: fiesta dinner
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer. (Add cheese last and cook until it melts.)

title: apricot mist punch
directions: Combine apricot nectar, pineapple juice, and concentrate in punch bowl.
Stir in ginger ale. Add ice ring with lime slices.

title: tuna log
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a blender.
Form log and chill. Roll log in mixture of pecans and parsley.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in fridge overnight to blend seasonings.
Slice bread into chunks; dip in mix.

title: whipped pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, whipped topping and 1 tablespoon of milk together.
Spread on bottom of pie crust.
Pour 1 cup of milk and 2 packages of pudding mix into bowl.
Stir until blended.
Add pumpkin and spices.
Blend again.
Spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Add topping. Dab when you serve. Serves 8.

title: bald knob church barbecues
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over meat and mix together.
Let set overnight before serving.

title: trisha's curried zucchini soup
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, curry, ginger and mustard in saucepan.
Add chicken broth and rice.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: saucy little meat loaves
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Make into 6 to 8 individual loaves.
Top with remaining ingredients, combined.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients only to a boil, then simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Strain into a gallon container.
Bring 2 cups of water to a boil; add 4 tea bags.
Steep.
Drain and add to first mixture.

title: candied yams
directions: Parboil sweet potatoes in skin.
Peel and cut in 1/4 pieces. Place in casserole dish in layers, sprinkling each layer with brown sugar and a little salt.
Dot with oleo and cinnamon.
Pour in 1/2 cup water.
Cover and bake until tender.
About half-way into baking, turn potato pieces over and add water if needed.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together.
Add Cool Whip and nuts. Chill.

title: pork tenderloin stuffed with applesauce
directions: Slit each tenderloin lengthwise to form pocket.
Place in baking dish. Pour juice into pockets.
Cover and marinate about 45 minutes at room temperature (for longer marinating refrigerate). Spray 10 x 15-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Fill slits with applesauce, peanuts and fennel seed and pepper. Secure with toothpicks.
Bake at 375° until registers 155° for 30 minutes or bake about 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fudge squares
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Combine the first and second mixtures.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix together biscuit mix, cheese and eggs.
Fold in zucchini and onion.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of mixture in frying pan. Fry 3 minutes for each side or until brown.
Makes 12.

title: hamburger bean pie
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Pour a thin mixture of corn bread mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until corn bread is done.

title: pumpkin-coconut bread
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine flour and next 7 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Alternate, adding flour mixture and pumpkin to sugar, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients all together. Add the milk and egg.

title: microwave pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared crust.
Heat 10 minutes, until pie is set.
Let stand until cool.
Garnish, if desired, with sweetened whipped cream.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a small bowl.
Blend well with wire whisk or fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice zucchini bake
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground meat. Add onion, rice, parsley, savory and water. Cover and cook until rice is tender, about 20 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste. Stir occasionally. Cut zucchini in half. Scoop out seeds and sprinkle with a little salt. Stuff with the rice and meat filling. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Cover with foil and place in a flat baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: mushroom dressing
directions: Melt butter; saut mushrooms slightly.
Add bread crumbs, onion juice, parsley, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Add sufficient broth or milk to moisten and mix well.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until browned; drain. Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes. Top with cheese. In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all. Cook at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: green tomato crisp pickles
directions: Soak tomato slices for 24 hours
in lime water made by stirring 3 cups of pickling lime into 2 gallons of water.
Drain and rinse well under water.
Soak 4 hours in fresh cold water, changing water every hour.
Drain.
Make syrup of remaining ingredients.
When they begin to boil, pour over the drained tomatoes.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, bring to a boil and boil for hour.
Put in jars and seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 9 or 10 pints.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cover chicken with water.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 40 minutes.
Save broth.
Saute celery and onion in margarine until soft.
Add flour and cook until brown.
Add broth from chicken, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles. Cook until tender.
Stir in chicken and half and half.
If the broth does not taste enough like chicken, add bouillon cubes to taste.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine pineapple, lemon and cranberry juices.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Refrigerate about 4 hours before serving.

title: egg nog
directions: Heat milk.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
When milk begins to simmer, slowly add egg mixture while beating continuously.
Cook over low heat until mixture coats spoon.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Add 1 cup of booze if desired.

title: strawberry peach upside-down cake
directions: Arrange peaches in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (I butter my pan well before I put peaches in).
Mix both Jell-Os and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Sprinkle 3/4 of mixture evenly over pieces and dot with butter.

title: oven chicken and potatoes
directions: Place all ingredients in a covered casserole dish in a 400° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chipper brownie
directions: Cover dates with a cup of boiling water and cool.
Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then dates and water.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan and cover with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken pasta supreme
directions: Dredge cutlets in flour, lightly coating both sides.
In 10-inch nonstick skillet, combine margarine and salt; heat until margarine is melted.
Add chicken; cook over medium heat until lightly browned.
Transfer chicken to plate; set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in oblong pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be topped with whipping cream.
This cake keeps excellent for several days.

title: crunchy molded salad
directions: In bowl, combine gelatin, salt and boiling water; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in the cold water, white pepper and the lime juice.
Chill until mixture is slightly thickened.
Fold cabbage, celery and yellow pepper into gelatin mixture.
Pour into each of 4 (3/4-cup) molds, dividing evenly.
Chill until firm for 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving contains 80 calories, 2.2 g protein, 19.4 carbohydrates, 0.1 g fat, 0 cholesterol and 336 mg sodium.

title: holiday potato dish
directions: Remove skins from potatoes and shred into a bowl.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup melted butter until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese.
Mix well. Turn onto greased 9x13 baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with corn flakes and drizzle with 3 tbsp butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Garnish with parsley.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream 1 1/2 cups margarine, shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with 1 cup pineapple, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cream remaining 1/2 cup margarine and confectioners sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Fold in remaining 1/2 cup pineapple.
Spoon over warm cake.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings.
Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan to 375°.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand beater until smooth.
Dip rings in batter, dripping excess in bowl.
Fry few rings at a time in oil until golden brown, about 2 minutes.

title: vegie delight
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on ungreased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Pinch seams together.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Spread next three ingredients on cooled crust. Put raw chopped vegetables on top: mushrooms, carrots, cauliflower and broccoli.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and keep in refrigerator.

title: michael's chewy charlies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add enough oats to thicken.
Drop by tablespoon onto buttered surface.

title: buck to robin's famous fajitas
directions: Marinate the meat in melted butter and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook slowly over hickory.
Cut onions, bell peppers and mushrooms into butter and fry until brown.
Add tomatoes and fry for 5 more minutes.
Add meat.
Serve with cheese, lettuce and tortillas.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Bring water, butter and minced onions to a boil.
Add broccoli and bring to a second boil.
Separate broccoli and stir in rice.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes, covered.
Add Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Mix well and place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with French fried onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican fiesta dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off excess fat.
In a crock-pot, combine all ingredients (cube up Velveeta cheese).
Heat on high for 30 minutes to melt.
Reduce to low and serve with tortilla chips.

title: fried chocolate sandwiches
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and butter.
Butter one side of all eight slices of bread.
Place 4 slices on griddle pan on medium-high heat.
Spread 1 rounded tablespoonful of mixture on each slice of bread and place remaining 4 slices of bread on top (sandwich style).
Cook on both sides until lightly browned.
Serve hot. Lightly dust with powdered sugar (optional).
It's sooo good!

title: dirt
directions: Chop up cookies and set aside.
Make pudding according to package directions.
Stir cool whip into prepared pudding.
In separate bowl mix cream cheese, butter and sugar together.
Use a deep glass bowl, layer the cream mixture with the chopped cookies. End with a layer of the cookies.
Can top with gummy worms or gummy bugs for kids party.

title: gator puppies
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients; add water, egg and cheese. Saute the ground gator in 1 tablespoon of margarine until the meat just turns white.
Drain and then add to mixture.
Stir by hand until all ingredients are distributed evenly.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon of mix into 375° oil and deep-fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with prepared honey-mustard dressing.
Makes approximately 250 (1 1/2-inch), in diameter.
Can substitute crab or fish.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt oleo on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Beat egg and add milk. Dip chicken in milk mixture, roll in flour mixture.
Place on cookie sheet, skin side down, on oleo.
Bake 30 minutes, turn pieces and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer in 375° oven.

title: roasted garlic
directions: Peel off outer layers of skin from whole garlic bulbs.
Leave bulb intact and cloves unpeeled.
Place bulbs in baking pan and drizzle with olive oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Fill pan with water until bulbs are half covered.
Cover pan tightly with foil. Bake at 425° for 1 hour. Break cloves off bulb and squeeze pulp onto bread.

title: surprise pizza
directions: Make some pizza dough.
Put sauce and cheese on top of dough. Grill pepperonis and put on top of the cheese.
Cook it in a pan in the oven for 13 hours.

title: butter cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches or three 8-inch round layer pans.
In large mixer bowl, mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat 5 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
On low speed, mix flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk; pour into pans.
Bake oblong at 450° for 50 minutes, layers at 300° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: cherry salad
directions: First Layer:
Crush the graham crackers and mix with the margarine.
Press into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch buttered dish.
Put aside 1 cup to sprinkle on top layer, if desired.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and shortening.
Press on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Toss 1/2 cup chocolate chips with flour. Stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Chill.

title: asparagus fold-overs
directions: Break asparagus spears into 3 to 4 inch pieces and cook until crisp tender.
Prepare hollandaise sauce according to directions on packet.
Cut crusts off bread slices. For each turnover, spread 1 tsp. hollandaise sauce on bread.

Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and put several slices of asparagus in the center of the bread. Fold one corner of bread over and secure with a wooden toothpick. Brush top with butter and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Repeat for remaining turnovers.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until browned.
Makes 8 turnovers.

title: chicken pot pie casserole
directions: Mix together and pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine until smooth.
Refrigerate in covered glass container. Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Same as Eagle Brand milk, but less fattening.

title: never fail pie meringue
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly; set aside.
Beat egg whites until frothy; continue beating, adding cooked mixture slowly.
Put on cooled pie filling of your choice.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Seedless grapes or mandarin oranges can be added.
Mix together ingredients and chill.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Gently stir in noodles, tuna and peas.
Cover and bake at 375° to 400° for 25 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with crushed chips.
Bake 10 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the flour, salt, baking powder and poppy seed in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Cream together 2 cups of the sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and 1 1/2 teaspoons of the almond extract in a medium bowl.
Add the dry ingredients to the sugar mixture alternately with the milk, ending with the dry ingredients.
Bake in 2 large greased loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 65 minutes.
Combine orange juice, 3/4 cup sugar and remaining 1/2 teaspoon almond extract and drizzle mixture over the top of baked bread.
Cool on wire rack.

title: pork chops and peaches
directions: Brown pork chops; season with salt and pepper.
Add chili sauce, lemon juice and peach juice drained from peach slices. Simmer for 50 minutes, or until tender.
Add sliced peaches; heat for 5 minutes.
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Wash raisins; cook 5 minutes in water and sugar.
Add butter and cool slightly.
Add beaten eggs.
Add raisins to dry ingredients; then add citron and nuts.
Bake in 8-inch tube pan that is greased and lined with waxed paper.
Cook slowly at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream together first four ingredients until light.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Fold in, alternating, flour, milk and flavoring.
Grease mold.
Add mixture.
Put in cold oven. Cook 1 hour and 35 minutes at 300°.
Do not open oven door until time is up.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Combine all together and melt in crock-pot.
Cook on low for approximately 2 hours.

title: rice and chicken wraps
directions: Cook chicken over medium high heat 10 to 12 minutes, lightly brown (cut into bite size pieces).
Add water and rice plus seasoning packet.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in salad dressing.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Bring 1 cup cranberry juice to a boil in saucepan; add gelatin, stirring to dissolve completely.
Stir in chilled cranberry juice. Chill until partially set.
Fold in apple, celery and walnuts. Pour into greased ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Partially thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Top with corn flakes and bake additional 5 minutes.

title: guess what cake
directions: Crumble by hand Ritz crackers.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar and vanilla to egg whites.
Fold this and black walnuts to the cracker crumbs.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 25 minutes only.

title: crock-pot beef
directions: Combine all in crock-pot.
Cook on low 8 to 12 hours (high for 5 to 6 hours).
Serve over noodles or with mashed potatoes.

title: fruit pizza torte
directions: Mix until crumbly and pat into a 12-inch round pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pookie's dip
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
Place all remaining ingredients into a crock-pot and heat, letting cheese melt.
Stir in meat mixture.
Serve with chips (tortillas) or assorted crackers.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Cook potatoes until just tender; cool, peel and cut into 1-inch thick slices.
Pare and core apples; slice into 1/2-inch rings.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Arrange potatoes and apples in alternate layers in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle part of the sugar-cinnamon mixture and lemon juice over each layer.
Dot with butter.
Add water.
Cover and bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Remove cover; cook for about 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini; add vanilla.
Mix.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
